66/*------ Argument & Expression Rewriting ----------*/
67int
68gen_islocal_index(int ast, int sptr, int dim, int subAst)
69{
70 int nargs, argt;
71 int newast;
72 int align;
73 int descr;
74 int olb, oub;
75 int tmp1, tmp2;
76
77 align = ALIGNG(sptr);
78 descr = DESCRG(sptr);
79 DESCUSEDP(sptr, TRUE);
80 if (!XBIT(47, 0x80) && align) {
81 /* inline it; if (idx.ge.sd$desc(olb).and.idx.le.sd$descr(oub)) then */
82 olb = check_member(ast, get_owner_lower(descr, dim));
83 oub = check_member(ast, get_owner_upper(descr, dim));
84 if (normalize_bounds(sptr)) {
85 olb = add_lbnd(DTYPEG(sptr), dim, olb, ast);
86 oub = add_lbnd(DTYPEG(sptr), dim, oub, ast);
87 }
88 tmp1 = mk_binop(OP_GE, subAst, olb, DT_LOG);
89 tmp2 = mk_binop(OP_LE, subAst, oub, DT_LOG);
90 newast = mk_binop(OP_LAND, tmp1, tmp2, DT_LOG);
91 return newast;
92 }
93
94 nargs = 3;
95 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
96 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = check_member(ast, mk_id(descr));
97 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = mk_cval(dim + 1, astb.bnd.dtype);
98 newast = mk_default_int(subAst);
99 if (normalize_bounds(sptr))
100 newast = sub_lbnd(DTYPEG(sptr), dim, newast, ast);
101 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) = newast;
102 newast = mk_func_node(A_FUNC,
103 mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_islocal_idx), DT_LOG)),
104 nargs, argt);
105 NODESCP(A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(newast)), 1);
106 A_DTYPEP(newast, DT_LOG);
107 return newast;
108} /* gen_islocal_index */

118#ifdef FLANG_FUNC_UNUSED
119/*
120 * SUM and PRODUCT reductions use a longer datatype for
121 * the reduction temporary; for instance, they use
122 * REAL*8 for a REAL*4 SUM call
123 */
124static int
125reduction_type(DTYPE dtype)
126{
127 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
128 case TY_BINT:
129 case TY_SINT:
130 case TY_INT:
131 return DT_INT;
132 case TY_INT8:
133 return dtype;
134
135 case TY_REAL:
136 return DT_REAL8;
137 case TY_DBLE:
138 if (XBIT(57, 0x14) || XBIT(51, 0x80)) {
139 /* no real*16, or map real*16 to real*8,
140 * or don't use quad precision accumulators */
141 return dtype;
142 } else {
143 return DT_QUAD;
144 }
145 case TY_QUAD:
146 return dtype;
147
148 case TY_CMPLX:
149 return DT_CMPLX16;
150 case TY_DCMPLX:
151 if (XBIT(57, 0x18) || XBIT(51, 0x80)) {
152 /* no complex*32, or map complex*32 to complex*16,
153 * or don't use quad precision accumulators */
154 return dtype;
155 } else {
156 return DT_QCMPLX;
157 }
158 case TY_QCMPLX:
159 return dtype;
160 default:
161 return dtype;
162 }
163} /* reduction_type */
164#endif
165
166#ifdef FLANG_FUNC_UNUSED
167static int
168assign_result(int sptr, int ast, DTYPE dtype, DTYPE dtyperes, int stdnext,
169 int lineno)
170{
171 int tsclr, tsclrAst, asn, std;
172 if (dtyperes == dtype)
173 return ast;
174 /* we had a SUM or PRODUCT where we used a REAL*8 temp for a REAL*4
175 * reduction, for instance. Now, coerce back to REAL*4 */
176 tsclr = sym_get_scalar(SYMNAME(sptr), "rr", dtyperes);
177 tsclrAst = mk_id(tsclr);
178 asn = mk_assn_stmt(tsclrAst, ast, dtyperes);
179 std = add_stmt_before(asn, stdnext);
180 STD_LINENO(std) = lineno;
181 STD_LOCAL(std) = 1;
182 STD_PAR(std) = STD_PAR(stdnext);
183 STD_TASK(std) = STD_TASK(stdnext);
184 STD_ACCEL(std) = STD_ACCEL(stdnext);
185 STD_KERNEL(std) = STD_KERNEL(stdnext);
186 return tsclrAst;
187} /* assign_result */
188#endif

190/* this will check whether cshift or eoshift needs any communication. */
191static LOGICAL
192is_no_comm_shift(int func_ast, int func_args)
193{
194 return TRUE;
195}
196
197/*
198 * generate inline loops for CSHIFT and EOSHIFT
199 */
200#define SHIFTMAX 7
201/* shift structure */
202static struct {
203 int shift; /* shift distance */
204 int dim, cdim; /* which dimension being shifted */
205 int boundary; /* for EOSHIFT, boundary value */
206 int shifttype; /* CSHIFT or EOSHIFT */
207 int dim_dest, dim_src; /* which dimensions get shifted */
208 int n, m, k; /* extent, positive shift amount */
209 int nc, mc, kc; /* constant value of above */
210 LOGICAL lt; /* less than */
211 LOGICAL then_part, else_part; /* nonzero shift, zero shift */
212} ss[SHIFTMAX]; /* shift data */
213
214static struct {
215 int shiftcount; /* how many nested shifts */
216 int subssrc[MAXSUBS], subsdest[MAXSUBS];
217 int src, dest;
218 int ndimsrc, ndimdest;
219} sg; /* shift global data */
220
221static void
222recurse_shift(int s)
223{
224 if (s < sg.shiftcount) {
225 handle_shift(s);
226 } else {
227 int ast_lhs, ast_rhs, ast;
228 ast_lhs =
229 mk_subscr(A_LOPG(sg.dest), sg.subsdest, sg.ndimdest, A_DTYPEG(sg.dest));
230 ast_rhs =
231 mk_subscr(A_LOPG(sg.src), sg.subssrc, sg.ndimsrc, A_DTYPEG(sg.src));
232 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ast_lhs, ast_rhs, DTY(A_DTYPEG(A_LOPG(sg.dest)) + 1));
233 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
234 }
235} /* recurse_shift */
236
237static void
238recurse_eoshift(int s)
239{
240 if (s < sg.shiftcount) {
241 handle_shift(s);
242 } else {
243 int ast_lhs, ast_rhs, ast;
244 ast_lhs =
245 mk_subscr(A_LOPG(sg.dest), sg.subsdest, sg.ndimdest, A_DTYPEG(sg.dest));
246 ast_rhs = ss[s - 1].boundary;
247 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ast_lhs, ast_rhs, DTY(A_DTYPEG(A_LOPG(sg.dest)) + 1));
248 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
249 }
250} /* recurse_eoshift */
251
252static void
253handle_shift(int s)
254{
255 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].m) != A_CNST) {
256 int ast, expr;
257 ast = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
258 expr = mk_binop(OP_NE, ss[s].m, astb.bnd.zero, DT_LOG);
259 A_IFEXPRP(ast, expr);
260 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
261 }
262 if (ss[s].then_part) {
263 int ta, la, ua, xa, lla, uua, sa;
264 int tb, lb, ub, xb, llb, uub, sb;
265 int tmp1, tmp2;
266 ta = sg.subsdest[ss[s].dim_dest];
267 la = A_LBDG(ta);
268 ua = A_UPBDG(ta);
269 sa = A_STRIDEG(ta);
270 xa = triplet_extent(ta);
271 tb = sg.subssrc[ss[s].dim_src];
272 lb = A_LBDG(tb);
273 ub = A_UPBDG(tb);
274 sb = A_STRIDEG(tb);
275 xb = triplet_extent(tb);
276 if (ss[s].shifttype == I_CSHIFT) {
277 /* a(la : ua - m*sa : sa) = b(lb + m*sb : ub : sb) */
278 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, ss[s].m, sa, astb.bnd.dtype);
279 uua = opt_binop(OP_SUB, ua, tmp1, astb.bnd.dtype);
280 sg.subsdest[ss[s].dim_dest] = mk_triple(la, uua, sa);
281
282 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, ss[s].m, sb, astb.bnd.dtype);
283 llb = opt_binop(OP_ADD, lb, tmp1, astb.bnd.dtype);
284 sg.subssrc[ss[s].dim_src] = mk_triple(llb, ub, sb);
285 recurse_shift(s + 1);
286
287 /* a(la + (n - m)*sa : ua : sa) = b(lb : ub - (n - m)*sb : sb) */
288 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_SUB, xa, ss[s].m, astb.bnd.dtype);
289 tmp2 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, tmp1, sa, astb.bnd.dtype);
290 lla = opt_binop(OP_ADD, la, tmp2, astb.bnd.dtype);
291 sg.subsdest[ss[s].dim_dest] = mk_triple(lla, ua, sa);
292
293 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_SUB, xb, ss[s].m, astb.bnd.dtype);
294 tmp2 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, tmp1, sb, astb.bnd.dtype);
295 uub = opt_binop(OP_SUB, ub, tmp2, astb.bnd.dtype);
296 sg.subssrc[ss[s].dim_src] = mk_triple(lb, uub, sb);
297 recurse_shift(s + 1);
298 } else if (ss[s].shifttype == I_EOSHIFT) {
299 int ast_lhs, ast_rhs, ast, x;
300 /* handle case with m > 0 */
301 x = 0;
302 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].m) == A_CNST) {
303 if (ss[s].mc > 0) {
304 x = 1;
305 }
306 } else {
307 int ast, expr;
308 x = 1;
309 /* test whether the shift distance is < 0 or > 0 */
310 ast = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
311 expr = mk_binop(OP_GT, ss[s].m, astb.bnd.zero, DT_LOG);
312 A_IFEXPRP(ast, expr);
313 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
314 }
315 if (x) {
316 /* a(la : ua - m*sa : sa) = b(lb + m*sb : ub : sb) */
317 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, ss[s].m, sa, astb.bnd.dtype);
318 uua = opt_binop(OP_SUB, ua, tmp1, astb.bnd.dtype);
319 sg.subsdest[ss[s].dim_dest] = mk_triple(la, uua, sa);
320
321 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, ss[s].m, sb, astb.bnd.dtype);
322 llb = opt_binop(OP_ADD, lb, tmp1, astb.bnd.dtype);
323 sg.subssrc[ss[s].dim_src] = mk_triple(llb, ub, sb);
324 recurse_shift(s + 1);
325
326 /* a(la + (n - m)*sa : ua : sa) = boundary */
327 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_SUB, xa, ss[s].m, astb.bnd.dtype);
328 tmp2 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, tmp1, sa, astb.bnd.dtype);
329 lla = opt_binop(OP_ADD, la, tmp2, astb.bnd.dtype);
330 sg.subsdest[ss[s].dim_dest] = mk_triple(lla, ua, sa);
331
332 ast_lhs = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(sg.dest), sg.subsdest, sg.ndimdest,
333 A_DTYPEG(sg.dest));
334 ast_rhs = ss[s].boundary; /* boundary have to be spread if array */
335 if (A_SHAPEG(ast_rhs)) {
336 /* add spread call */
337 int newargt, spread;
338 newargt = mk_argt(3);
339 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = ast_rhs;
340 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = mk_cval(ss[s].dim_dest + 1, astb.bnd.dtype);
341 tmp2 = opt_binop(OP_SUB, ua, lla, astb.bnd.dtype);
342 if (sa != astb.i1 && sa != astb.bnd.one) {
343 tmp2 = opt_binop(OP_DIV, tmp2, sa, astb.bnd.dtype);
344 }
345 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mk_cval(tmp2, astb.bnd.dtype);
346 spread = mk_id(intast_sym[I_SPREAD]);
347 ast_rhs = mk_func_node(A_INTR, spread, 3, newargt);
348 A_OPTYPEP(ast_rhs, I_SPREAD);
349 }
350 ast =
351 mk_assn_stmt(ast_lhs, ast_rhs, DTY(A_DTYPEG(A_LOPG(sg.dest)) + 1));
352 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
353 }
354 /* handle case with m < 0 */
355 x = 0;
356 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].m) == A_CNST) {
357 if (ss[s].mc < 0) {
358 x = 1;
359 }
360 } else {
361 int ast;
362 x = 1;
363 ast = mk_stmt(A_ELSE, 0);
364 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
365 }
366 if (x) {
367 /* a(la - m*sa : ua : sa) = b(lb : ub - m*sb : sb) */
368 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, ss[s].m, sa, astb.bnd.dtype);
369 lla = opt_binop(OP_SUB, la, tmp1, astb.bnd.dtype);
370 sg.subsdest[ss[s].dim_dest] = mk_triple(lla, ua, sa);
371
372 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_MUL, ss[s].m, sb, astb.bnd.dtype);
373 uub = opt_binop(OP_SUB, ub, tmp1, astb.bnd.dtype);
374 sg.subssrc[ss[s].dim_src] = mk_triple(lb, uub, sb);
375 recurse_shift(s + 1);
376
377 /* a(la : (la-m*sa)-1 : sa) = boundary */
378 lla = opt_binop(OP_SUB, lla, astb.bnd.one, astb.bnd.dtype);
379 sg.subsdest[ss[s].dim_dest] = mk_triple(la, lla, sa);
380
381 ast_lhs = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(sg.dest), sg.subsdest, sg.ndimdest,
382 A_DTYPEG(sg.dest));
383 ast_rhs = ss[s].boundary; /* boundary have to be spread if array */
384 if (A_SHAPEG(ast_rhs)) {
385 /* add spread call */
386 int newargt, spread;
387 newargt = mk_argt(3);
388 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = ast_rhs;
389 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = mk_cval(ss[s].dim_dest + 1, astb.bnd.dtype);
390 tmp2 = opt_binop(OP_SUB, ua, lla, astb.bnd.dtype);
391 if (sa != astb.i1 && sa != astb.bnd.one) {
392 tmp2 = opt_binop(OP_DIV, tmp2, sa, astb.bnd.dtype);
393 }
394 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mk_cval(tmp2, astb.bnd.dtype);
395 spread = mk_id(intast_sym[I_SPREAD]);
396 ast_rhs = mk_func_node(A_INTR, spread, 3, newargt);
397 A_OPTYPEP(ast_rhs, I_SPREAD);
398 }
399 ast =
400 mk_assn_stmt(ast_lhs, ast_rhs, DTY(A_DTYPEG(A_LOPG(sg.dest)) + 1));
401 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
402 }
403 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].m) != A_CNST) {
404 int ast;
405 ast = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
406 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
407 }
408 }
409
410 sg.subsdest[ss[s].dim_dest] = ta;
411 sg.subssrc[ss[s].dim_src] = tb;
412 }
413
414 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].m) != A_CNST) {
415 int ast;
416 ast = mk_stmt(A_ELSE, 0);
417 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
418 }
419
420 if (ss[s].else_part) {
421 /* a(la:ua:sa) = b(lb:ub:sb) */
422 if (ss[s].shifttype == I_EOSHIFT)
423 recurse_eoshift(s + 1);
424 else
425 recurse_shift(s + 1);
426 }
427
428 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].m) != A_CNST) {
429 int ast;
430 ast = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
431 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
432 }
433} /* handle_shift */
434
435/*
436 * for an EOSHIFT call with an omitted boundary value,
437 * use zero. This functions returns an AST referencing
438 * an appropriate 'zero' value for the given array datatype.
439 */
440static int
441_makezero(DTYPE dtype)
442{
443 int v[4], sptr;
444 INT V;
445 int sub, ndims, i;
446 int firstast, lastast, ast, member;
447 char *str;
448 int l, len;
449 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
450 case TY_HOLL:
451 case TY_WORD:
452 case TY_INT:
453 case TY_LOG:
454 case TY_REAL:
455 case TY_SINT:
456 case TY_BINT:
457 case TY_SLOG:
458 case TY_BLOG:
459 V = 0;
460 return mk_cval1(V, dtype);
461
462 case TY_DBLE:
463 case TY_QUAD:
464 case TY_DWORD:
465 case TY_LOG8:
466 case TY_INT8:
467 v[0] = v[1] = v[2] = v[3] = 0;
468 sptr = getcon(v, dtype);
469 return mk_cval1((INT)sptr, dtype);
470
471 case TY_CMPLX:
472 v[0] = stb.flt0;
473 v[1] = stb.flt0;
474 sptr = getcon(v, dtype);
475 return mk_cval(sptr, dtype);
476 case TY_DCMPLX:
477 v[0] = stb.dbl0;
478 v[1] = stb.dbl0;
479 sptr = getcon(v, dtype);
480 return mk_cval1(sptr, dtype);
481 case TY_QCMPLX:
482 v[0] = v[1] = v[2] = v[3] = 0;
483 v[0] = getcon(v, DT_QUAD);
484 v[1] = v[0];
485 sptr = getcon(v, dtype);
486 return mk_cval1(sptr, dtype);
487
488 case TY_CHAR:
489 case TY_NCHAR:
490 /* make blank */
491 len = DTY(dtype + 1);
492 if (!A_ALIASG(len)) {
493 len = 1;
494 } else {
495 len = A_ALIASG(len);
496 len = A_SPTRG(len);
497 len = CONVAL2G(len);
498 }
499 str = (char *)malloc(len + 1);
500 for (l = 0; l < len; ++l)
501 str[l] = ' ';
502 str[len] = '\0';
503 sptr = getstring(str, len);
504 free(str);
505 return mk_id(sptr);
506 break;
507
508 case TY_ARRAY:
509 /* make an array of zeros */
510 sub = _makezero(DTY(dtype + 1));
511 ndims = ADD_NUMDIM(dtype);
512 for (i = 0; i < ndims; ++i) {
513 int j, extent, prevast, ast;
514 extent = ADD_EXTNTAST(dtype, i);
515 if (!A_ALIASG(extent)) {
516 extent = 1;
517 } else {
518 extent = A_ALIASG(extent);
519 extent = A_SPTRG(extent);
520 extent = CONVAL2G(extent);
521 }
522 prevast = 0;
523 for (j = 0; j < extent; ++j) {
524 ast = mk_init(sub, DTY(dtype + 1));
525 A_RIGHTP(ast, prevast);
526 prevast = ast;
527 }
528 sub = ast;
529 }
530 return sub;
531
532 case TY_STRUCT:
533 case TY_DERIVED:
534 /* make a structure of zeros */
535 firstast = 0;
536 lastast = 0;
537 for (member = DTY(dtype + 1); member > NOSYM; member = SYMLKG(member)) {
538 sub = _makezero(DTYPEG(member));
539 ast = mk_init(sub, DTYPEG(member));
540 if (firstast == 0) {
541 firstast = ast;
542 } else {
543 A_RIGHTP(lastast, ast);
544 }
545 lastast = ast;
546 A_SPTRP(ast, member);
547 }
548 return firstast;
549
550 case TY_UNION:
551 case TY_PTR:
552 case TY_NONE:
553 default:
554 interr("makezero: unknown datatype", DTY(dtype), 4);
555 break;
556 }
557 return 0;
558} /* _makezero */
559
560/*
561 * write data-initialization to dinit file for array/structure
562 */
563static void
564putzero(int ast)
565{
566 /* derived type? */
567 for (; ast; ast = A_RIGHTG(ast)) {
568 int a, dtype, sptr;
569 a = A_LEFTG(ast);
570 switch (A_TYPEG(a)) {
571 case A_INIT:
572 dtype = A_DTYPEG(a);
573 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED || DTY(dtype) == TY_STRUCT) {
574 if (DTY(dtype + 3)) {
575 dinit_put(DINIT_TYPEDEF, DTY(dtype + 3));
576 }
577 }
578 putzero(a);
579 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED || DTY(dtype) == TY_STRUCT) {
580 if (DTY(dtype + 3)) {
581 dinit_put(DINIT_ENDTYPE, DTY(dtype + 3));
582 }
583 }
584 break;
585 case A_ID:
586 case A_CNST:
587 sptr = A_SPTRG(a);
588 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
589 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
590 case TY_BINT:
591 case TY_SINT:
592 case TY_INT:
593 case TY_BLOG:
594 case TY_SLOG:
595 case TY_LOG:
596 case TY_FLOAT:
597 dinit_put(dtype, CONVAL2G(sptr));
598 break;
599 case TY_DBLE:
600 case TY_CMPLX:
601 case TY_DCMPLX:
602 case TY_QUAD:
603 case TY_QCMPLX:
604 case TY_INT8:
605 case TY_LOG8:
606 case TY_CHAR:
607 dinit_put(dtype, sptr);
608 break;
609 }
610 break;
611 }
612 }
613} /* putzero */
614
615/*
616 * for an EOSHIFT call with an omitted boundary value,
617 * use zero. This functions returns an AST referencing
618 * an appropriate 'zero' value for the given array datatype.
619 */
620static int
621makezero(DTYPE dtype)
622{
623 int sub, sptr;
624 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
625 default:
626 return _makezero(dtype);
627
628 case TY_ARRAY:
629 /* make an array of zeros */
630 sub = _makezero(dtype);
631 sptr = get_next_sym("init", "r");
632 STYPEP(sptr, ST_ARRAY);
633 DTYPEP(sptr, dtype);
634 SCP(sptr, SC_STATIC);
635 DINITP(sptr, 1);
636 SEQP(sptr, 1);
637 PARAMP(sptr, 1);
638 PARAMVALP(sptr, sub);
639 dinit_put(DINIT_LOC, sptr);
640 putzero(sub);
641 dinit_put(DINIT_END, 0);
642 return mk_id(sptr);
643
644 case TY_STRUCT:
645 case TY_UNION:
646 case TY_DERIVED:
647 /* make an array of zeros */
648 sub = _makezero(dtype);
649 sptr = get_next_sym("init", "r");
650 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
651 DTYPEP(sptr, dtype);
652 SCP(sptr, SC_STATIC);
653 DINITP(sptr, 1);
654 SEQP(sptr, 1);
655 PARAMP(sptr, 1);
656 PARAMVALP(sptr, sub);
657 /* dump out the values to the data initialization file */
658 dinit_put(DINIT_LOC, sptr);
659 if (DTY(dtype + 3)) {
660 dinit_put(DINIT_TYPEDEF, DTY(dtype + 3));
661 }
662 putzero(sub);
663 if (DTY(dtype + 3)) {
664 dinit_put(DINIT_ENDTYPE, DTY(dtype + 3));
665 }
666 dinit_put(DINIT_END, 0);
667 return mk_id(sptr);
668 }
669} /* makezero */
670
671static void
672inline_shifts(int func_ast, int func_args, int lhs)
673{
674 int srcarray;
675 int s;
676
677 int sptrsrc, sptrdest;
678 int asdsrc, asddest;
679 int count;
680 int i;
681 int args;
682
683 sg.shiftcount = 0;
684 srcarray = func_ast;
685 args = func_args;
686 /* find all nested cshift/eoshift calls */
687 while (A_TYPEG(srcarray) == A_INTR) {
688 if (A_OPTYPEG(srcarray) == I_CSHIFT) {
689 /* cshift(array, shift, [dim]) */
690 assert(sg.shiftcount < SHIFTMAX, "inline_shifts: too many nested shifts",
691 func_ast, 3);
692 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(args, 0);
693 s = sg.shiftcount;
694 ss[s].shift = ARGT_ARG(args, 1);
695 ss[s].dim = ARGT_ARG(args, 2);
696 ss[s].shifttype = I_CSHIFT;
697 } else if (A_OPTYPEG(srcarray) == I_EOSHIFT) {
698 /* eoshift(array, shift, [boundary, dim]); */
699 assert(sg.shiftcount < SHIFTMAX, "inline_shifts: too many nested shifts",
700 func_ast, 3);
701 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(args, 0);
702 s = sg.shiftcount;
703 ss[s].shift = ARGT_ARG(args, 1);
704 ss[s].boundary = ARGT_ARG(args, 2);
705 if (ss[s].boundary == 0) {
706 /* must create a 'zero' */
707 if (DTY(A_DTYPEG(srcarray)) == TY_ARRAY) {
708 ss[s].boundary = makezero(DTY(A_DTYPEG(srcarray) + 1));
709 } else {
710 ss[s].boundary = makezero(A_DTYPEG(srcarray));
711 }
712 }
713 ss[s].dim = ARGT_ARG(args, 3);
714 ss[s].shifttype = I_EOSHIFT;
715 } else {
716 interr("inline_shifts: must be CSHIFT or EOSHIFT", srcarray, 3);
717 }
718 if (ss[s].dim == 0)
719 ss[s].dim = mk_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);
720 assert(A_TYPEG(ss[s].dim) == A_CNST,
721 "inline_shifts: variable dimension not implemented", srcarray, 3);
722 ss[s].cdim = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(ss[s].dim)));
723 ++sg.shiftcount;
724 args = A_ARGSG(srcarray);
725 }
726 assert(lhs, "inline_shifts: no lhs", func_ast, 3);
727 assert(A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_ID || A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_SUBSCR ||
728 A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_MEM,
729 "inline_shifts: bad lhs type", func_ast, 3);
730 assert(A_TYPEG(srcarray) == A_ID || A_TYPEG(srcarray) == A_SUBSCR ||
731 A_TYPEG(srcarray) == A_MEM,
732 "inline_shifts: bad source type", func_ast, 3);
733
734 sg.src = convert_subscript(srcarray);
735 sg.dest = convert_subscript(lhs);
736 sptrsrc = memsym_of_ast(sg.src);
737 sptrdest = memsym_of_ast(sg.dest);
738
739 asdsrc = A_ASDG(sg.src);
740 sg.ndimsrc = ASD_NDIM(asdsrc);
741 for (s = 0; s < sg.shiftcount; ++s) {
742 if (ss[s].cdim > sg.ndimsrc || (ss[s].cdim < 1 || ss[s].cdim > 7)) {
743 error(504, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptrsrc), CNULL);
744 ss[s].cdim = 1;
745 }
746 }
747 count = 0;
748 for (i = 0; i < sg.ndimsrc; ++i) {
749 if (A_TYPEG(ASD_SUBS(asdsrc, i)) == A_TRIPLE ||
750 A_SHAPEG(ASD_SUBS(asdsrc, i))) {
751 ++count;
752 for (s = 0; s < sg.shiftcount; ++s) {
753 if (count == ss[s].cdim) {
754 ss[s].dim_src = i;
755 break;
756 }
757 }
758 }
759 }
760
761 asddest = A_ASDG(sg.dest);
762 sg.ndimdest = ASD_NDIM(asddest);
763 count = 0;
764 for (i = 0; i < sg.ndimdest; ++i) {
765 if (A_TYPEG(ASD_SUBS(asddest, i)) == A_TRIPLE ||
766 A_SHAPEG(ASD_SUBS(asddest, i))) {
767 ++count;
768 for (s = 0; s < sg.shiftcount; ++s) {
769 if (count == ss[s].cdim) {
770 ss[s].dim_dest = i;
771 break;
772 }
773 }
774 }
775 }
776
777 /* Determine the section extent */
778 for (s = 0; s < sg.shiftcount; ++s) {
779 ss[s].n = triplet_extent(ASD_SUBS(asdsrc, ss[s].dim_src));
780 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].n) != A_CNST) {
781 int tmp, ast;
782 tmp = sym_get_scalar("n", "s", astb.bnd.dtype);
783 ast = mk_assn_stmt(mk_id(tmp), ss[s].n, astb.bnd.dtype);
784 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
785 ss[s].n = mk_id(tmp);
786 } else {
787 ss[s].nc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(ss[s].n)));
788 }
789
790 /* Determine the net positive shift amount for CSHIFT
791 * m = MOD(k, n)
792 * if (m .lt. 0) then
793 * m = n + m
794 * endif
795 */
796
797 ss[s].k = ss[s].shift;
798 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].k) == A_CNST && A_TYPEG(ss[s].n) == A_CNST) {
799 int result;
800 ss[s].kc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(ss[s].k)));
801 result = ss[s].kc % ss[s].nc;
802 ss[s].m = mk_cval(result, astb.bnd.dtype);
803 } else {
804 int mod, tmp, ast;
805 mod = ast_intr(I_MOD, DT_INT, 2, ss[s].k, ss[s].n);
806 tmp = sym_get_scalar("m", "s", astb.bnd.dtype);
807 ss[s].m = mk_id(tmp);
808 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ss[s].m, mod, astb.bnd.dtype);
809 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
810 }
811 ss[s].lt = TRUE;
812 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].m) == A_CNST) {
813 ss[s].mc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(ss[s].m)));
814 if (ss[s].mc >= 0) {
815 ss[s].lt = FALSE;
816 } else if (ss[s].shifttype == I_CSHIFT) {
817 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].n) == A_CNST) {
818 ss[s].mc = ss[s].mc + ss[s].nc;
819 ss[s].m = mk_cval(ss[s].mc, astb.bnd.dtype);
820 ss[s].lt = FALSE;
821 } else {
822 int ast, tmp;
823 ast = opt_binop(OP_ADD, ss[s].m, ss[s].n, astb.bnd.dtype);
824 tmp = sym_get_scalar("m", "s", astb.bnd.dtype);
825 ss[s].m = mk_id(tmp);
826 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ss[s].m, ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
827 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
828 }
829 }
830 }
831
832 if (ss[s].lt && ss[s].shifttype == I_CSHIFT) {
833 int ast, expr;
834 ast = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
835 expr = mk_binop(OP_LT, ss[s].m, astb.bnd.zero, DT_LOG);
836 A_IFEXPRP(ast, expr);
837 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
838 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ss[s].m,
839 opt_binop(OP_ADD, ss[s].n, ss[s].m, astb.bnd.dtype),
840 astb.bnd.dtype);
841 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
842 ast = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
843 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
844 }
845
846 ss[s].then_part = FALSE;
847 ss[s].else_part = FALSE;
848 if (A_TYPEG(ss[s].m) != A_CNST) {
849 ss[s].then_part = TRUE;
850 ss[s].else_part = TRUE;
851 } else if (ss[s].mc != 0) {
852 ss[s].then_part = TRUE;
853 } else {
854 ss[s].else_part = TRUE;
855 }
856 }
857 for (i = 0; i < sg.ndimdest; ++i) {
858 sg.subsdest[i] = ASD_SUBS(asddest, i);
859 }
860 for (i = 0; i < sg.ndimsrc; ++i) {
861 sg.subssrc[i] = ASD_SUBS(asdsrc, i);
862 }
863
864 handle_shift(0);
865
866} /* inline_shifts */
867
868/* Determine the section extent
869 * n = (ub - lb + sb) / sb
870 */
871static int
872triplet_extent(int t)
873{
874 int lb, ub, sb;
875 int tmp1, tmp2, tmp3;
876
877 assert(A_TYPEG(t) == A_TRIPLE, "triplet_extent: should be triplet", t, 3);
878 lb = A_LBDG(t);
879 ub = A_UPBDG(t);
880 sb = A_STRIDEG(t);
881 tmp1 = opt_binop(OP_SUB, ub, lb, astb.bnd.dtype);
882 tmp2 = opt_binop(OP_ADD, tmp1, sb, astb.bnd.dtype);
883 tmp3 = opt_binop(OP_DIV, tmp2, sb, astb.bnd.dtype);
884 return tmp3;
885}
886
887static LOGICAL
888is_inline_overlap_shifts(int func_ast, int func_args, int lhs)
889{
890 return FALSE;
891}
892
893LOGICAL
894is_shift_conflict(int func_ast, int func_args, int expr)
895{
896 int srcarray;
897 int boundary;
898 int sptr;
899
900 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
901 sptr = memsym_of_ast(srcarray);
902 boundary = -1;
903 if (A_OPTYPEG(func_ast) == I_EOSHIFT)
904 boundary = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
905 if (A_OPTYPEG(func_ast) == I_CSHIFT)
906 if (expr && is_another_shift(expr, sptr, I_EOSHIFT, boundary))
907 return TRUE;
908 if (A_OPTYPEG(func_ast) == I_EOSHIFT) {
909 if (expr && is_another_shift(expr, sptr, I_CSHIFT, boundary))
910 return TRUE;
911 if (expr && is_another_shift(expr, sptr, I_EOSHIFT, boundary))
912 return TRUE;
913 }
914 return FALSE;
915}
916
917static struct {
918 int sptr;
919 int type;
920 int boundary;
921} expp;
922
923static LOGICAL
924is_another_shift(int expr, int sptr, int type, int boundary)
925{
926 LOGICAL result = FALSE;
927
928 expp.sptr = sptr;
929 expp.type = type;
930 expp.boundary = boundary;
931 ast_visit(1, 1);
932 ast_traverse(expr, _is_another_shift, NULL, &result);
933 ast_unvisit();
934 return result;
935}
936
937static LOGICAL
938_is_another_shift(int targast, LOGICAL *pflag)
939{
940 int boundary;
941 int sptr;
942 int type;
943 int srcarray;
944 int args;
945 int check_boundary;
946
947 if (A_TYPEG(targast) == A_INTR) {
948 if (A_OPTYPEG(targast) == I_CSHIFT || A_OPTYPEG(targast) == I_EOSHIFT) {
949 type = A_OPTYPEG(targast);
950 args = A_ARGSG(targast);
951 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(args, 0);
952 boundary = 0;
953 if (type == I_EOSHIFT)
954 boundary = ARGT_ARG(args, 2);
955 sptr = 0;
956 switch (A_TYPEG(srcarray)) {
957 case A_ID:
958 case A_SUBSCR:
959 sptr = memsym_of_ast(srcarray);
960 break;
961 }
962 check_boundary = 1;
963 if (expp.boundary != -1)
964 if (expp.boundary == boundary)
965 check_boundary = 0;
966 if (expp.sptr == sptr && expp.type == type && check_boundary) {
967 *pflag = TRUE;
968 return TRUE;
969 }
970 }
971 }
972 return FALSE;
973}
974
975static int
976stride_one(int lw, int up)
977{
978 if (A_TYPEG(lw) == A_CNST && A_TYPEG(up) == A_CNST &&
979 ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(lw)) > ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(up)))
980 return mk_isz_cval((ISZ_T)-1, astb.bnd.dtype);
981 return astb.bnd.one;
982}
983
984int
985convert_subscript(int a)
986{
987 ADSC *ad;
988 int sptr, parent, member;
989 int ndim;
990 int lb, ub, st;
991 int i;
992 int subs[MAXSUBS];
993 int asd;
994
995 if (A_TYPEG(a) == A_ID) {
996 sptr = A_SPTRG(a);
997 if (!is_array_type(sptr))
998 return a;
999 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
1000 ndim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
1001 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
1002 subs[i] = mk_triple(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i),
1003 stride_one(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i)));
1004 }
1005 return mk_subscr(mk_id(sptr), subs, ndim, A_DTYPEG(a));
1006 }
1007
1008 if (A_TYPEG(a) == A_MEM) {
1009 /* do the parent first */
1010 parent = convert_subscript(A_PARENTG(a));
1011 member = A_MEMG(a);
1012 a = mk_member(parent, member, A_DTYPEG(member));
1013 sptr = A_SPTRG(member);
1014 if (!is_array_type(sptr))
1015 return a;
1016 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
1017 ndim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
1018 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
1019 subs[i] = mk_triple(check_member(a, AD_LWAST(ad, i)),
1020 check_member(a, AD_UPAST(ad, i)), astb.bnd.one);
1021 }
1022 return mk_subscr(a, subs, ndim, A_DTYPEG(a));
1023 }
1024
1025 if (A_TYPEG(a) == A_SUBSCR) {
1026 int lop, anytriple;
1027 sptr = sptr_of_subscript(a);
1028 assert(is_array_type(sptr), "convert_subscript: must be array", 2, a);
1029 lop = A_LOPG(a);
1030 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
1031 asd = A_ASDG(a);
1032 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
1033 anytriple = 0;
1034 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
1035 subs[i] = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
1036 if (A_TYPEG(subs[i]) == A_TRIPLE) {
1037 anytriple = 1;
1038 lb = A_LBDG(subs[i]);
1039 if (!lb)
1040 lb = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
1041 ub = A_UPBDG(subs[i]);
1042 if (!ub)
1043 ub = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
1044 st = A_STRIDEG(subs[i]);
1045 if (!st)
1046 st = astb.bnd.one;
1047 subs[i] = mk_triple(lb, ub, st);
1048 }
1049 }
1050 /* was the triplet at this level? */
1051 if (anytriple)
1052 return mk_subscr(lop, subs, ndim, A_DTYPEG(a));
1053
1054 if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_MEM) {
1055 parent = convert_subscript(A_PARENTG(lop));
1056 member = A_MEMG(lop);
1057 lop = mk_member(parent, member, A_DTYPEG(member));
1058 }
1059 return mk_subscr(lop, subs, ndim, A_DTYPEG(a));
1060 }
1061 assert(0, "convert_subscript: it must be array", 0, a);
1062 return a;
1063}
1064
1065static int
1066convert_subscript_in_expr(int expr)
1067{
1068 int l, r, d, o;
1069 int i, nargs, argt;
1070 int newargt;
1071
1072 if (expr == 0)
1073 return expr;
1074 switch (A_TYPEG(expr)) {
1075 /* expressions */
1076 case A_BINOP:
1077 o = A_OPTYPEG(expr);
1078 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
1079 l = convert_subscript_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr));
1080 r = convert_subscript_in_expr(A_ROPG(expr));
1081 return mk_binop(o, l, r, d);
1082 case A_UNOP:
1083 o = A_OPTYPEG(expr);
1084 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
1085 l = convert_subscript_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr));
1086 return mk_unop(o, l, d);
1087 case A_CONV:
1088 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
1089 l = convert_subscript_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr));
1090 if (DT_ISSCALAR(A_DTYPEG(l)) && DTY(d) == TY_ARRAY) {
1091 return mk_promote_scalar(l, d, A_SHAPEG(expr));
1092 } else {
1093 return mk_convert(l, d);
1094 }
1095 case A_PAREN:
1096 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
1097 l = convert_subscript_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr));
1098 return mk_paren(l, d);
1099 case A_SUBSTR:
1100 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
1101 o = convert_subscript_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr));
1102 l = convert_subscript_in_expr(A_LEFTG(expr));
1103 r = convert_subscript_in_expr(A_RIGHTG(expr));
1104 return mk_substr(o, l, r, d);
1105 case A_INTR:
1106 /* some intrinsic calls get shared trees, so make new tree */
1107 /* leave present alone */
1108 if (A_OPTYPEG(expr) == I_PRESENT)
1109 return expr;
1110 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(expr);
1111 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
1112 argt = A_ARGSG(expr);
1113 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
1114 ARGT_ARG(newargt, i) = convert_subscript_in_expr(ARGT_ARG(argt, i));
1115 }
1116 l = mk_func_node(A_INTR, A_LOPG(expr), nargs, newargt);
1117 A_DTYPEP(l, A_DTYPEG(expr));
1118 A_OPTYPEP(l, A_OPTYPEG(expr));
1119 A_SHAPEP(l, A_SHAPEG(expr));
1120 return l;
1121 case A_FUNC:
1122 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(expr);
1123 argt = A_ARGSG(expr);
1124 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
1125 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) = convert_subscript_in_expr(ARGT_ARG(argt, i));
1126 }
1127 return expr;
1128 case A_CNST:
1129 case A_CMPLXC:
1130 return expr;
1131 case A_MEM:
1132 case A_ID:
1133 case A_SUBSCR:
1134 if (!A_SHAPEG(expr))
1135 return expr;
1136 expr = convert_subscript(expr);
1137 return expr;
1138 default:
1139 interr("convert_subscript_in_expr: unknown expression", expr, 2);
1140 return expr;
1141 }
1142}
1143
1144static LOGICAL
1145stride1_triple(int triple)
1146{
1147#if DEBUG
1148 assert(A_TYPEG(triple) == A_TRIPLE, "stride1_triple: not A_TRIPLE", triple,
1149 4);
1150#endif
1151 if (A_STRIDEG(triple) && A_STRIDEG(triple) != astb.i1 &&
1152 A_STRIDEG(triple) != astb.bnd.one)
1153 return FALSE;
1154 return TRUE;
1155}
1156
1157LOGICAL
1158contiguous_section(int arr_ast)
1159{
1160 int asd;
1161 int ndims, dim;
1162 int astsub;
1163 int sptr;
1164 int ast1;
1165 LOGICAL nonfull = FALSE;
1166
1167 /* only for data references */
1168 if (A_TYPEG(arr_ast) != A_ID && A_TYPEG(arr_ast) != A_SUBSCR &&
1169 A_TYPEG(arr_ast) != A_MEM)
1170 return FALSE;
1171
1172 for (ast1 = arr_ast; A_TYPEG(ast1) == A_MEM || A_TYPEG(ast1) == A_SUBSCR;
1173 ast1 = A_PARENTG(ast1)) {
1174 if (!A_SHAPEG(ast1))
1175 return TRUE; /* everything is contiguous so far and no more subscripting
1176 */
1177 if (A_TYPEG(ast1) == A_MEM) {
1178 /* must be the first and only member */
1179 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(ast1));
1180 if (ADDRESSG(sptr) != 0 || SYMLKG(sptr) != NOSYM)
1181 return FALSE;
1182 } else if (A_TYPEG(ast1) == A_SUBSCR) {
1183 /* must be contiguous subscripting */
1184 asd = A_ASDG(ast1);
1185 ndims = ASD_NDIM(asd);
1186 /* Find the 1st non-scalar dimension. */
1187 for (dim = ndims - 1; dim >= 0; --dim) {
1188 int ss = ASD_SUBS(asd, dim);
1189 if (A_TYPEG(ss) == A_TRIPLE)
1190 break;
1191 if (A_SHAPEG(ss))
1192 return FALSE; /* non-triplet shaped subscript */
1193 }
1194 if (dim < 0) {
1195 nonfull = TRUE; /* all parent subscripts must be scalar as well */
1196 } else if (nonfull) {
1197 return FALSE; /* already had a deeper non-full dimension */
1198 } else {
1199 astsub = ASD_SUBS(asd, dim);
1200 sptr = memsym_of_ast(ast1);
1201 if (!stride1_triple(astsub))
1202 return FALSE; /* not-stride-1 */
1203 if (!is_whole_dim(ast1, dim))
1204 nonfull = TRUE;
1205 /* Leading dimensions must be full. */
1206 for (--dim; dim >= 0; --dim) {
1207 if (!is_whole_dim(ast1, dim))
1208 return FALSE;
1209 }
1210 }
1211 }
1212 }
1213 if (A_TYPEG(ast1) != A_ID)
1214 return FALSE;
1215 return TRUE;
1216}
1217
1218/* Check if array section is contiguous, does not have to be whole array */
1219static LOGICAL
1220contiguous_section_array(int arr_ast)
1221{
1222 int asd, ss;
1223 int ndims, dim;
1224 int ast1 = A_TYPEG(arr_ast) == A_MEM ? A_MEMG(arr_ast) : arr_ast;
1225
1226 if (!ast1)
1227 return FALSE;
1228
1229 if (!A_SHAPEG(ast1) || A_TYPEG(ast1) == A_ID)
1230 return TRUE;
1231 asd = A_ASDG(ast1);
1232 ndims = ASD_NDIM(asd);
1233 for (dim = ndims - 1; dim >= 0; dim--) {
1234 ss = ASD_SUBS(asd, dim);
1235 if (A_TYPEG(ss) == A_TRIPLE) {
1236 continue;
1237 }
1238 if (A_TYPEG(ss) == A_SUBSCR) {
1239 if (!is_whole_dim(arr_ast, dim))
1240 return FALSE;
1241 }
1242 if (A_TYPEG(ss) == A_ID && (DTY(A_DTYPEG(ss))) == TY_ARRAY) {
1243 if (!is_whole_dim(arr_ast, dim))
1244 return FALSE;
1245 }
1246 }
1247 return TRUE;
1248}
1249
1250static int
1251extract_shape_from_args(int func_ast)
1252{
1253 int funcsptr, iface;
1254 int dscptr;
1255 int dummy_sptr;
1256 int shape = A_SHAPEG(func_ast);
1257 int arg_shape;
1258 int argt;
1259 int nargs;
1260 int i;
1261
1262 funcsptr = procsym_of_ast(A_LOPG(func_ast));
1263 proc_arginfo(funcsptr, NULL, &dscptr, &iface);
1264 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(func_ast);
1265 argt = A_ARGSG(func_ast);
1266 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
1267 if (dscptr) {
1268 dummy_sptr = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + i];
1269 if (ARGT_ARG(argt, i) == astb.ptr0 && OPTARGG(dummy_sptr)) {
1270 continue;
1271 }
1272 }
1273 arg_shape = A_SHAPEG(ARGT_ARG(argt, i));
1274 /* scalars are always conformable */
1275 if (arg_shape) {
1276 if (shape) {
1277 if (!conform_shape(arg_shape, shape) &&
1278 ((iface && FVALG(iface)) || !dummy_sptr ||
1279 INTENTG(dummy_sptr) != INTENT_IN)) {
1280 error(508, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(funcsptr), CNULL);
1281 break;
1282 }
1283 } else {
1284 shape = arg_shape;
1285 }
1286 }
1287 }
1288 return shape;
1289}
1290
1291static int alloc_char_temp(int, const char *, int, int, int);
1292static int get_charintrin_temp(int, const char *);
1293
1294static struct {
1295 int continue_std, func_std;
1296} difficult = {0, 0};
1297
1298void
1299check_pointer_type(int past, int tast, int stmt, LOGICAL is_sourced_allocation)
1300{
1301 /* For type pointers, we want to set the type field of its
1302 * descriptor to whatever type we're assigning it to. Used for
1303 * polymorphic entities. The flag argument is set when we call this
1304 * function due to a sourced allocation.
1305 */
1306
1307 int psptr, tsptr, dt1, dt2, desc1, type2;
1308 int astnew, is_inline, intrin_type;
1309 static int tmp = 0;
1310 int nullptr;
1311 bool isNullAssn = false;
1312
1313 if (DT_PTR == DT_INT8)
1314 nullptr = astb.k0;
1315 else
1316 nullptr = astb.i0;
1317 if (A_TYPEG(tast) == A_SUBSCR)
1318 tast = A_LOPG(tast);
1319
1320 dt1 = A_DTYPEG(past);
1321 if (DTY(dt1) == TY_ARRAY) {
1322 dt1 = DTY(dt1 + 1);
1323 }
1324 dt2 = A_DTYPEG(tast);
1325 if (DTY(dt2) == TY_ARRAY) {
1326 dt2 = DTY(dt2 + 1);
1327 }
1328
1329 if (DTY(dt1) != TY_DERIVED) {
1330 return;
1331 }
1332
1333 if (DTY(dt2) != TY_DERIVED) {
1334 if (!UNLPOLYG(DTY(dt1 + 3))) {
1335 return;
1336 }
1337 intrin_type = 1;
1338 } else {
1339 intrin_type = 0;
1340 }
1341
1342 psptr = memsym_of_ast(past);
1343
1344 if (!CLASSG(psptr)) {
1345 return;
1346 }
1347
1348 switch (A_TYPEG(tast)) {
1349 case A_ID:
1350 case A_LABEL:
1351 case A_ENTRY:
1352 case A_SUBSCR:
1353 case A_SUBSTR:
1354 case A_MEM:
1355 tsptr = memsym_of_ast(tast);
1356 break;
1357 case A_INTR:
1358 if (A_OPTYPEG(tast) == I_NULL) {
1359 tsptr = psptr;
1360 isNullAssn = true;
1361 break;
1362 }
1363 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
1364 default:
1365 return;
1366 }
1367
1368 if (ALLOCDESCG(psptr)) {
1369 desc1 = DESCRG(psptr);
1370 DESCUSEDP(psptr, TRUE);
1371 if (!desc1 || SDSCG(psptr)) {
1372 desc1 = SDSCG(psptr);
1373 }
1374 if (!intrin_type) {
1375 if (CLASSG(tsptr) || (is_sourced_allocation && ALLOCATTRG(tsptr))) {
1376 type2 = get_type_descr_arg(gbl.currsub, tsptr);
1377 } else {
1378 type2 = getccsym('P', tmp++, ST_VAR);
1379 DTYPEP(type2, dt2);
1380 type2 = get_static_type_descriptor(type2);
1381 }
1382 } else {
1383 type2 = dtype_to_arg(dt2);
1384 type2 = mk_cval1(type2, DT_INT);
1385 type2 = mk_unop(OP_VAL, type2, DT_INT);
1386 }
1387
1388 /*
1389 * Beware! If intrin_type is TRUE, 'type2' is the index of an AST (that
1390 * corresponds to the code number of the intrinsic type). But if it's
1391 * false, 'type2' is a symbol table pointer (to a descriptor).
1392 */
1393 if (desc1 && type2 && !XBIT(68, 0x4)) {
1394
1395 if (isNullAssn) {
1396 int src_ast, astnew;
1397 if (intrin_type) {
1398 src_ast = type2;
1399 } else {
1400 type2 = getccsym('P', tmp++, ST_VAR);
1401 DTYPEP(type2, dt2);
1402 type2 = get_static_type_descriptor(type2);
1403 src_ast = mk_id(type2);
1404 }
1405 if (STYPEG(psptr) != ST_MEMBER) {
1406 astnew = mk_set_type_call(mk_id(desc1), src_ast, intrin_type);
1407 } else {
1408 int sdsc_mem = get_member_descriptor(psptr);
1409 int dest_ast = check_member(past, mk_id(sdsc_mem));
1410 astnew = mk_set_type_call(dest_ast, src_ast, intrin_type);
1411 }
1412 add_stmt_after(astnew, stmt);
1413 return;
1414 }
1415
1416 if (STYPEG(psptr) != ST_MEMBER &&
1417 (STYPEG(tsptr) != ST_MEMBER || !CLASSG(tsptr))) {
1418 is_inline = (!intrin_type)
1419 ? inline_RTE_set_type(desc1, type2, stmt, 1, dt2, 0)
1420 : 0;
1421 if (!is_inline) {
1422 int dest_ast = mk_id(desc1);
1423 int src_ast =
1424 intrin_type ? type2 : check_member(dest_ast, mk_id(type2));
1425
1426 gen_set_type(dest_ast, src_ast, stmt, FALSE, intrin_type);
1427 }
1428 } else if ((STYPEG(psptr) == ST_MEMBER && (STYPEG(tsptr) != ST_MEMBER)) ||
1429 !CLASSG(tsptr)) {
1430 int sdsc_mem = get_member_descriptor(psptr);
1431 assert(sdsc_mem > NOSYM, "no descriptor for member", psptr, 3);
1432 is_inline = 0; /* TBD: inline_RTE_set_type( ) */
1433 if (!is_inline) {
1434 int nz_ast, if_ast, ptr_ast;
1435 int dest_ast = check_member(past, mk_id(sdsc_mem));
1436 int src_ast =
1437 intrin_type ? type2 : check_member(dest_ast, mk_id(type2));
1438 astnew = mk_set_type_call(dest_ast, src_ast, intrin_type);
1439 ptr_ast = mk_unop(OP_LOC, A_PARENTG(past), DT_PTR);
1440 nz_ast = mk_binop(OP_NE, ptr_ast, nullptr, DT_LOG);
1441 if_ast = mk_stmt(A_IF, 0);
1442 A_IFEXPRP(if_ast, nz_ast);
1443 A_IFSTMTP(if_ast, astnew);
1444 /* Use add_stmt_after() instead of add_stmt_before() below.
1445 * This appears to be the right thing to do in the event that you
1446 * have something like recordPtr%next => recordPtr2.
1447 * We want to access next's descriptor (embedded in recordPtr),
1448 * but we have to do it before we assign/change recordPtr%next
1449 * address.
1450 */
1451 add_stmt_before(if_ast, stmt);
1452 }
1453 } else if (STYPEG(psptr) != ST_MEMBER && STYPEG(tsptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
1454 int sdsc_mem = get_member_descriptor(tsptr);
1455 assert(sdsc_mem > NOSYM, "no descriptor for member", tsptr, 3);
1456 is_inline = 0; /* TBD: inline_RTE_set_type( ) */
1457 if (!is_inline) {
1458 int nz_ast, if_ast, ptr_ast;
1459 int dest_ast = mk_id(desc1);
1460 int src_ast =
1461 intrin_type
1462 ? type2
1463 : mk_member(A_PARENTG(tast), mk_id(sdsc_mem), A_DTYPEG(tast));
1464 astnew = mk_set_type_call(dest_ast, src_ast, intrin_type);
1465
1466 /* if (tast .ne. 0) */
1467
1468 ptr_ast = mk_unop(OP_LOC, A_PARENTG(tast), DT_PTR);
1469 nz_ast = mk_binop(OP_NE, ptr_ast, nullptr, DT_LOG);
1470 if_ast = mk_stmt(A_IF, 0);
1471 A_IFEXPRP(if_ast, nz_ast);
1472 A_IFSTMTP(if_ast, astnew);
1473 /* Use add_stmt_after() instead of add_stmt_before() below.
1474 * This appears to be the right thing to do in the event that you
1475 * have something like recordPtr => recordPtr%next. We want to
1476 * access next's descriptor (embedded in recordPtr), but we have to
1477 * do it before we assign/change recordPtr's address.
1478 */
1479 add_stmt_before(if_ast, stmt);
1480 }
1481 } else {
1482 int sdsc_mem = get_member_descriptor(tsptr);
1483 int sdsc_mem2 = get_member_descriptor(psptr);
1484 assert(sdsc_mem > NOSYM, "no descriptor for member", tsptr, 3);
1485 assert(sdsc_mem2 > NOSYM, "no descriptor for member", psptr, 3);
1486 is_inline = 0; /* TBD: inline_RTE_set_type( ) */
1487 if (!is_inline) {
1488 int nz_ast, if_ast, ptr_ast;
1489 int dest_ast =
1490 mk_member(A_PARENTG(past), mk_id(sdsc_mem2), A_DTYPEG(past));
1491 int src_ast =
1492 intrin_type
1493 ? type2
1494 : mk_member(A_PARENTG(tast), mk_id(sdsc_mem), A_DTYPEG(tast));
1495 astnew = mk_set_type_call(dest_ast, src_ast, intrin_type);
1496
1497 /* if (tast .ne. 0) */
1498 ptr_ast = mk_unop(OP_LOC, A_PARENTG(tast), DT_PTR);
1499 nz_ast = mk_binop(OP_NE, ptr_ast, nullptr, DT_LOG);
1500 if_ast = mk_stmt(A_IF, 0);
1501 A_IFEXPRP(if_ast, nz_ast);
1502 A_IFSTMTP(if_ast, astnew);
1503 /* Use add_stmt_after() instead of add_stmt_before() below.
1504 * This appears to be the right thing to do in the event that you
1505 * have something like recordPtr%next => recordPtr%next%next.
1506 * We want to access next's descriptor (embedded in recordPtr),
1507 * but we have to do it before we assign/change recordPtr%next
1508 * address.
1509 */
1510 add_stmt_before(if_ast, stmt);
1511 }
1512 }
1513 }
1514 }
1515
1516 if (!is_sourced_allocation && POINTERG(psptr) && UNLPOLYG(DTY(dt1 + 3)) &&
1517 UNLPOLYG(DTY(dt2 + 3)) && SDSCG(psptr) && SDSCG(tsptr)) {
1518 /* init unlimited polymorphic descriptor for pointer.
1519 * We do not have to do this for the sourced allocation case since
1520 * the sourced allocation case is handled in semant3.c with the
1521 * ALLOCATE productions.
1522 */
1523 int psdsc, tsdsc, dest_sdsc_ast, src_sdsc_ast;
1524 int fsptr, argt, val, ast;
1525 if (STYPEG(psptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
1526 psdsc = get_member_descriptor(psptr);
1527 } else {
1528 psdsc = SDSCG(psptr);
1529 }
1530 assert(psdsc > NOSYM, "no descriptor for psptr", psptr, 3);
1531 if (STYPEG(tsptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
1532 tsdsc = get_member_descriptor(tsptr);
1533 } else if (SCG(tsptr) == SC_DUMMY) {
1534 tsdsc = get_type_descr_arg(gbl.currsub, tsptr);
1535 } else {
1536 tsdsc = SDSCG(tsptr);
1537 }
1538 assert(tsdsc > NOSYM, "no descriptor for tsptr", tsptr, 3);
1539 fsptr = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_init_unl_poly_desc), DT_NONE);
1540 dest_sdsc_ast = check_member(past, mk_id(psdsc));
1541 src_sdsc_ast = check_member(tast, mk_id(tsdsc));
1542
1543 argt = mk_argt(3);
1544 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = dest_sdsc_ast;
1545 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = src_sdsc_ast;
1546 val = mk_cval1(43, DT_INT);
1547 val = mk_unop(OP_VAL, val, DT_INT);
1548 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) = val;
1549 ast = mk_id(fsptr);
1550 ast = mk_func_node(A_CALL, ast, 3, argt);
1551 add_stmt_after(ast, stmt);
1552 }
1553}
1554
1555/* Given one of the arguments to move_alloc (either from or to), return the
1556 * corresponding symbol and pointer to the arg. */
1557static void
1558move_alloc_arg(int arg, SPTR *sptr, int *pvar)
1559{
1560 if (A_TYPEG(arg) == A_ID)
1561 *sptr = A_SPTRG(arg);
1562 else if (A_TYPEG(arg) == A_MEM)
1563 *sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(arg));
1564 else
1565 *sptr = 0;
1566
1567 if (MIDNUMG(*sptr)) {
1568 *pvar = check_member(arg, mk_id(MIDNUMG(*sptr)));
1569 } else if (!ALLOCATTRG(*sptr)) {
1570 error(507, ERR_Fatal, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(*sptr), 0);
1571 } else {
1572 *pvar = mk_unop(OP_LOC, mk_id(*sptr), DT_PTR);
1573 }
1574}
1575
1576void
1577check_alloc_ptr_type(int psptr, int stmt, DTYPE dt1, int flag, LOGICAL after,
1578 int past, int astmem)
1579{
1580 /* For allocatable/pointer objects, we assign a type to its dynamic type.
1581 * The psptr is the sptr of the allocatable/pointer object.
1582 * The stmt arg is the current statement to insert the type assign.
1583 * The typespec is the dynamic type. If it's 0, we assign the object's
1584 * declared type to its dynamic type.
1585 * The flag arg is set when we want to assign type to psptr's descriptor. It's
1586 * also set to 2 when psptr is used as an actual arg passed to a unlimited
1587 * polymorphic argument.
1588 * If flag is not set, then we just want to reserve space for type in
1589 * psptr's descriptor.
1590 * The after flag is set when we want to insert the type assignment after
1591 * the current statement. If it's 0, then we insert it before current stmt.
1592 */
1593
1594 LOGICAL intrin_type;
1595 LOGICAL no_alloc_ptr = FALSE;
1596
1597 if (dt1 <= DT_NONE)
1598 dt1 = DTYPEG(psptr);
1599 if (is_array_dtype(dt1))
1600 dt1 = array_element_dtype(dt1);
1601 intrin_type = DTY(dt1) != TY_DERIVED;
1602
1603 if (!ALLOCDESCG(psptr) && !is_array_dtype(DTYPEG(psptr))) {
1604 if (!SDSCG(psptr) || DTY(DTYPEG(psptr)) == TY_DERIVED) {
1605 set_descriptor_rank(TRUE);
1606 get_static_descriptor(psptr);
1607 set_descriptor_rank(FALSE);
1608 ALLOCDESCP(psptr, TRUE);
1609 no_alloc_ptr = TRUE;
1610 } else if (flag == 2 && (ALLOCATTRG(psptr) || POINTERG(psptr))) {
1611 /* allocatable or pointer actual and unlimited polymorphic dummy */
1612 set_descriptor_rank(TRUE);
1613 get_static_descriptor(psptr);
1614 set_descriptor_rank(FALSE);
1615 if (ALLOCATTRG(psptr))
1616 ALLOCDESCP(psptr, TRUE);
1617 }
1618 }
1619
1620 if (intrin_type) {
1621 DTYPE dt2 = DTYPEG(psptr);
1622 if (is_array_dtype(dt2))
1623 dt2 = array_element_dtype(dt2);
1624 if (flag != 2 && (DTY(dt2) != TY_DERIVED || !UNLPOLYG(DTY(dt2 + 3)))) {
1625 /* ignore non-derived type and unlimited polymorphic objects
1626 * unless flag is set to 2.
1627 */
1628 flag = 0;
1629 }
1630 /* otherwise we are allocating an intrinsic type to an unlimited polymorphic
1631 * object */
1632 }
1633
1634 if (flag != 0 && (ALLOCDESCG(psptr) || intrin_type)) {
1635 int desc1_sptr = 0;
1636 LOGICAL is_member = past && STYPEG(psptr) == ST_MEMBER &&
1637 (CLASSG(psptr) || FINALIZEDG(psptr));
1638 if (is_member) {
1639 /* copy type into member type descriptor.*/
1640 desc1_sptr = get_member_descriptor(psptr);
1641 } else {
1642 desc1_sptr = SDSCG(psptr);
1643 if (!desc1_sptr)
1644 desc1_sptr = DESCRG(psptr);
1645 if (desc1_sptr)
1646 DESCUSEDP(psptr, TRUE);
1647 }
1648 if (desc1_sptr) {
1649 int type2_sptr = 0, type2_ast = 0;
1650 if (intrin_type) {
1651 type2_ast = mk_cval1(dtype_to_arg(dt1), DT_INT);
1652 type2_ast = mk_unop(OP_VAL, type2_ast, DT_INT);
1653 } else {
1654 static int tmp = 0;
1655 type2_sptr = getccsym('A', tmp++, ST_VAR);
1656 DTYPEP(type2_sptr, dt1);
1657 type2_sptr = get_static_type_descriptor(type2_sptr);
1658 if (type2_sptr > NOSYM)
1659 type2_ast = mk_id(type2_sptr);
1660 }
1661 if (is_member ||
1662 (type2_ast && !XBIT(68, 0x4) &&
1663 (intrin_type || !inline_RTE_set_type(desc1_sptr, type2_sptr, stmt,
1664 after, dt1, astmem)))) {
1665 int desc1_ast = get_desc_tag(desc1_sptr);
1666 int tagdesc = get_desc_tag(desc1_sptr);
1667 if (is_member) {
1668 desc1_ast = check_member(past, desc1_ast);
1669 tagdesc = check_member(past, tagdesc);
1670
1671 } else if (astmem) {
1672 desc1_ast = check_member(astmem, desc1_ast);
1673 tagdesc = check_member(astmem, tagdesc);
1674 }
1675 stmt = gen_set_type(desc1_ast, type2_ast, stmt, !after, intrin_type);
1676 if (no_alloc_ptr) {
1677 int tag = mk_isz_cval(intrin_type ? __TAGPOLY : __TAGDESC, DT_INT);
1678 int astnew = mk_assn_stmt(tagdesc, tag, 0);
1679 stmt = add_stmt_before(astnew, stmt);
1680 }
1681 }
1682 }
1683 }
1684}
1685
1686/* if argument(s) is non-member allocatable, ALLOCDESC must be
1687 * set because RTE_sect2 can be called, then full descriptor must
1688 * be passed. They can be arguments to other routine before matmul
1689 * and can be allocated in the subroutine.
1690 */
1691static void
1692check_arg_isalloc(int arg)
1693{
1694 int lop;
1695 int sptr = 0;
1696 if (A_TYPEG(arg) == A_SUBSCR) {
1697 lop = A_LOPG(arg);
1698 if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_ID)
1699 sptr = A_SPTRG(lop);
1700 } else if (A_TYPEG(arg) == A_ID) {
1701 sptr = A_SPTRG(arg);
1702 }
1703 if (sptr && ALLOCATTRG(sptr)) {
1704 ALLOCDESCP(sptr, 1);
1705 }
1706}
1707
1708static int forall_indx[MAXSUBS];
1709
1710static LOGICAL
1711id_dep_in_forall_idxlist(int ast)
1712{
1713 int i;
1714
1715 for (i = 0; forall_indx[i] && i < MAXSUBS; i++) {
1716 if (A_SPTRG(ast) == forall_indx[i]) {
1717 return TRUE;
1718 }
1719 }
1720 return 0;
1721}
1722
1723static LOGICAL
1724_arg_forall_depnd(int ast, int *is_dep)
1725{
1726 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ID) {
1727 *is_dep = id_dep_in_forall_idxlist(ast);
1728 return TRUE;
1729 }
1730
1731 return FALSE;
1732}
1733
1734static void
1735init_idx_list(int forall)
1736{
1737 int triplet_list;
1738 int i;
1739
1740 for (i = 0; i < MAXSUBS; i++)
1741 forall_indx[i] = 0;
1742
1743 triplet_list = A_LISTG(forall);
1744 for (i = 0; i < MAXSUBS && triplet_list;
1745 i++, triplet_list = ASTLI_NEXT(triplet_list)) {
1746 forall_indx[i] = ASTLI_SPTR(triplet_list);
1747 }
1748}
1749
1750static LOGICAL
1751charintr_arg_forall_depnd(int ast_arg)
1752{
1753 LOGICAL is_dep = FALSE;
1754 int asd;
1755 int ndims;
1756 int i;
1757
1758 if (A_TYPEG(ast_arg) != A_SUBSCR) {
1759 return FALSE;
1760 }
1761
1762 init_idx_list(STD_AST(arg_gbl.std));
1763
1764 asd = A_ASDG(ast_arg);
1765 ndims = ASD_NDIM(asd);
1766 for (i = 0; i < ndims && !is_dep; i++) {
1767 ast_visit(1, 1);
1768 ast_traverse(ASD_SUBS(asd, i), _arg_forall_depnd, NULL, &is_dep);
1769 ast_unvisit();
1770 }
1771 return is_dep;
1772}
1773
1774/** \brief func_ast is a function or intrinsic call. If it is a
1775 transformational intrinsic, create an appropriate temp, rewrite, and return
1776 a load of that temp.
1777 For now, don't do anything with user-defined functions.
1778 \param func_ast A_INTR, A_FUNC, or A_ICALL
1779 \param func_args rewritten args for the function
1780 \param lhs ast for lhs (temp) if non-zero
1781
1782 If lhs is non-zero, check lhs to see if it is OK for the intended
1783 use; if so, return 0.
1784 */
1785static int
1786rewrite_func_ast(int func_ast, int func_args, int lhs)
1787{
1788 int shape = A_SHAPEG(func_ast);
1789 DTYPE dtype = A_DTYPEG(func_ast);
1790 int dim, ndims, cdim;
1791 int shift;
1792 int newsym;
1793 int temp_arr = 0;
1794 int newargt;
1795 int srcarray;
1796 int rank;
1797 int retval = 0;
1798 int ast;
1799 int nargs;
1800 int mask;
1801 int value;
1802 LOGICAL back;
1803 int is_back_true;
1804 int vector;
1805 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn;
1806 const char *root;
1807 int i;
1808 int subscr[MAXSUBS];
1809 int sptr;
1810 int astnew;
1811 int temp_sptr;
1812 LOGICAL is_icall; /* iff its first arg is changable */
1813 int ast_from_len = 0;
1814 int arg1;
1815 int dtnew;
1816 LOGICAL forall_depnd_intrin;
1817 const int type = A_TYPEG(func_ast);
1818 const int optype = A_OPTYPEG(func_ast);
1819
1820 /* it only handles calls */
1821 if (type != A_INTR && type != A_FUNC && type != A_ICALL) {
1822 return func_ast;
1823 }
1824 if (type == A_FUNC) {
1825 if (elemental_func_call(func_ast)) {
1826 shape = extract_shape_from_args(func_ast);
1827 }
1828 goto ret_norm;
1829 }
1830 if (type == A_ICALL) {
1831 switch (optype) {
1832 case I_MOVE_ALLOC:
1833 transform_move_alloc(func_ast, func_args);
1834 return -1;
1835 case I_MVBITS:
1836 transform_mvbits(func_ast, func_args);
1837 return -1;
1838 case I_MERGE:
1839 transform_merge(func_ast, func_args);
1840 return -1;
1841 case I_NULLIFY:
1842 return -1;
1843#ifdef I_C_F_POINTER
1844 case I_C_F_POINTER:
1845 transform_c_f_pointer(func_ast, func_args);
1846 return -1;
1847#endif
1848#ifdef I_C_F_POINTER
1849 case I_C_F_PROCPOINTER:
1850 transform_c_f_procpointer(func_ast, func_args);
1851 return -1;
1852#endif
1853 }
1854 }
1855 if (type == A_INTR && optype == I_ASSOCIATED) {
1856 return transform_associated(arg_gbl.std, func_ast);
1857 }
1858
1859 if (type == A_INTR) {
1860 switch (optype) {
1861 case I_ADJUSTL: /* adjustl(string) */
1862 case I_ADJUSTR: /* adjustr(string) */
1863 if (STYPEG(A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(func_ast))) == ST_PD)
1864 /* it's an IK_ELEMENTAL, but needs special processing */
1865 break;
1866 /*
1867 * ADJUSTL/ADJUSTR has been replaced, so this A_INTR
1868 * is just a function call
1869 */
1870 goto ret_norm;
1871 default:
1872 if (INKINDG(A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(func_ast))) == IK_ELEMENTAL)
1873 goto ret_norm;
1874 }
1875 }
1876 is_icall = TRUE;
1877 switch (optype) {
1878 case I_NUMBER_OF_PROCESSORS:
1879 retval = mk_id(sym_mknproc());
1880 A_DTYPEP(retval, DT_INT);
1881 A_SHAPEP(retval, 0);
1882 return retval;
1883 case I_ALL: /* all(mask, [dim]) */
1884 case I_ANY: /* any(mask, [dim]) */
1885 case I_COUNT: /* count(mask, [dim]) */
1886 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
1887 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
1888
1889 /* check dim range if constant */
1890 cdim = -1;
1891 if (dim != 0 && A_TYPEG(dim) == A_CNST) {
1892 cdim = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(dim)));
1893 if (A_SHAPEG(srcarray) &&
1894 ((int)SHD_NDIM(A_SHAPEG(srcarray)) < cdim || 1 > cdim))
1895 error(505, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(func_ast))), CNULL);
1896 }
1897
1898 if (shape == 0 && (dim == 0 || cdim != -1)) {
1899 /*E.g., pghpf_anys(result, mask) */
1900 rtlRtn =
1901 optype == I_ALL ? RTE_alls : optype == I_ANY ? RTE_anys : RTE_counts;
1902 nargs = 2;
1903 } else {
1904 /* E.g., pghpf_any(result, mask, dim) */
1905 rtlRtn =
1906 optype == I_ALL ? RTE_all : optype == I_ANY ? RTE_any : RTE_count;
1907 nargs = 3;
1908 }
1909 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
1910 if (dim == 0) {
1911 dim = mk_cval(0, DT_INT);
1912 }
1913 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
1914 if (nargs == 3) {
1915 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = dim;
1916 }
1917 goto ret_new;
1918 case I_PRODUCT: /* product(array, [dim, mask]) */
1919 case I_SUM: /* sum(array, [dim, mask]) */
1920 mask = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
1921
1922 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
1923 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
1924
1925 /* check dim range if constant */
1926 cdim = -1;
1927 if (dim != 0 && A_TYPEG(dim) == A_CNST) {
1928 cdim = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(dim)));
1929 if (A_SHAPEG(srcarray) &&
1930 ((int)SHD_NDIM(A_SHAPEG(srcarray)) < cdim || 1 > cdim))
1931 error(505, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(func_ast))), CNULL);
1932 if (!XBIT(47, 0x80) && !XBIT(70, 0x1000000) && cdim == 1 && mask == 0) {
1933 /* Other than meeting the usual requirements, continue with
1934 * transforming the call if we inhibit inlining reductions
1935 * controlled by XBIT(47,0x80); otherwise, an ICE,
1936 * "rewrite_func_ast: bad dim for sum/prod" will occur
1937 * in an ensuing call
1938 */
1939 return func_ast;
1940 }
1941 }
1942 if (mask == 0) {
1943 mask = mk_cval(1, DT_LOG);
1944 }
1945
1946 if (shape == 0 && (dim == 0 || cdim != -1)) {
1947 /* E.g,. pghpf_sums(result, array, mask) */
1948 rtlRtn = optype == I_PRODUCT ? RTE_products : RTE_sums;
1949 nargs = 3;
1950 } else {
1951 /* E.g., pghpf_sum(result, array, mask, dim) */
1952 rtlRtn = optype == I_PRODUCT ? RTE_product : RTE_sum;
1953 nargs = 4;
1954 }
1955
1956 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
1957 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
1958 mask = misalignment(srcarray, mask, arg_gbl.std);
1959 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mask;
1960 if (nargs == 4) {
1961 assert(dim != 0, "rewrite_func_ast: bad dim for sum/prod", func_ast, 4);
1962 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = dim;
1963 }
1964 goto ret_new;
1965 case I_EXECUTE_COMMAND_LINE:
1966 nargs = 7;
1967 rtlRtn = RTE_execcmdline;
1968 newsym = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), DT_INT);
1969 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
1970 for (i = 0; i < nargs - 1; i++) {
1971 int arg = ARGT_ARG(func_args, i);
1972 ARGT_ARG(newargt, i) = arg != 0 ? arg : i == 0 ? astb.ptr0c : astb.ptr0;
1973 }
1974 /* Add two extra arguments at the end of the execute_command_line argument
1975 list. Those two integer kind for the exitstat and cmdstat argument
1976 respectively.
1977 */
1978 ARGT_ARG(newargt, nargs - 2) = mk_cval(size_of(stb.user.dt_int), DT_INT4);
1979 ARGT_ARG(newargt, nargs - 1) = mk_cval(size_of(stb.user.dt_int), DT_INT4);
1980 is_icall = FALSE;
1981 goto ret_call;
1982 case I_NORM2: /* norm2(array, [dim]) */
1983 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
1984 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
1985 rank = get_ast_rank(srcarray);
1986 shape = dim ? A_SHAPEG(srcarray) : 0;
1987
1988 // If dim is supplied for a one dimensional array, result is still a scalar.
1989 shape = (shape && (rank == 1)) ? 0 : shape;
1990
1991 if (dim == 0) {
1992 rtlRtn = RTE_norm2_nodim;
1993 nargs = 3;
1994 } else {
1995 rtlRtn = RTE_norm2;
1996 nargs = 4;
1997 }
1998 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
1999 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2000
2001 if (!flg.ieee) { // fast. Currently also mapped to relaxed
2002 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mk_cval(1, DT_INT4);
2003 } else { // Precise
2004 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mk_cval(2, DT_INT4);
2005 }
2006
2007 if (nargs == 4) {
2008 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = dim;
2009 }
2010 goto ret_new;
2011 case I_MAXVAL: /* maxval(array, [dim, mask]) */
2012 case I_MINVAL: /* minval(array, [dim, mask]) */
2013 mask = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2014 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2015 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2016
2017 if (mask == 0) {
2018 mask = mk_cval(1, DT_LOG);
2019 }
2020 mask = misalignment(srcarray, mask, arg_gbl.std);
2021
2022 if (dim == 0) {
2023 rtlRtn = optype == I_MAXVAL ? RTE_maxvals : RTE_minvals;
2024 nargs = 3;
2025 } else {
2026 rtlRtn = optype == I_MAXVAL ? RTE_maxval : RTE_minval;
2027 nargs = 4;
2028 }
2029 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2030 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2031 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mask;
2032 if (nargs == 4) {
2033 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = dim;
2034 }
2035 goto ret_new;
2036 case I_CSHIFT: /* cshift(array, shift, [dim]) */
2037 if (A_SHAPEG(ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1)))
2038 goto unch;
2039 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2040 if (dim == 0)
2041 dim = mk_cval(1, DT_INT);
2042 if (A_TYPEG(dim) != A_CNST)
2043 goto unch;
2044 /* don't inline forall(i=1:n) a(i,:) = cshift(b(i,:)) */
2045
2046 if (!arg_gbl.inforall &&
2047 is_inline_overlap_shifts(func_ast, func_args, lhs))
2048 goto ret_norm;
2049 if (!is_no_comm_shift(func_ast, func_args))
2050 goto unch;
2051 if (arg_gbl.inforall)
2052 goto unch;
2053 /* the following can inline cshift and eoshift
2054 * (without no_comm or comm restriction )
2055 * but it is restricted no_comm shift for performance reason only
2056 */
2057
2058 assert(shape != 0, "expected non-zero shape", 0, ERR_Fatal);
2059 /* need to put this into a temp */
2060 temp_arr = mk_result_sptr(func_ast, func_args, subscr, DTY(dtype + 1), lhs,
2061 &retval);
2062 if (temp_arr != 0) {
2063 mk_mem_allocate(mk_id(temp_arr), subscr, arg_gbl.std, 0);
2064 mk_mem_deallocate(mk_id(temp_arr), arg_gbl.std);
2065 }
2066 inline_shifts(func_ast, func_args, retval);
2067 return temp_arr == 0 && lhs != 0 ? 0 : retval;
2068
2069 unch:
2070 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2071 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2072 if (dim == 0)
2073 dim = mk_cval(1, DT_INT);
2074 shift = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2075 nargs = 4;
2076 if (A_SHAPEG(shift) == 0) {
2077 shift = convert_int(shift, astb.bnd.dtype);
2078 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_cshiftsca : RTE_cshifts;
2079 } else {
2080 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_cshiftca : RTE_cshift;
2081 }
2082 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2083 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2084 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = shift;
2085 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = convert_int(dim, astb.bnd.dtype);
2086 goto ret_new;
2087
2088 case I_DOT_PRODUCT: /* dot_product(vector_a, vector_b) */
2089 nargs = 3;
2090 rtlRtn = RTE_dotpr;
2091 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2092 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2093 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2094 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2095 goto ret_new;
2096 case I_EOSHIFT: /* eoshift(array, shift, [boundary, dim]); */
2097 if (A_SHAPEG(ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1)))
2098 goto eoshiftcall; /* shift not a scalar */
2099
2100 if (!arg_gbl.inforall &&
2101 is_inline_overlap_shifts(func_ast, func_args, lhs))
2102 goto ret_norm;
2103
2104 if (!is_no_comm_shift(func_ast, func_args))
2105 goto eoshiftcall;
2106 if (A_TYPEG(ARGT_ARG(func_args, 3)) != A_CNST)
2107 goto eoshiftcall;
2108 if (arg_gbl.inforall)
2109 goto eoshiftcall;
2110 /* the following can inline cshift and eoshift
2111 * (without no_comm or comm restriction )
2112 * but it is restricted no_comm shift for performance reason only
2113 */
2114
2115 if (shape) {
2116 /* need to put this into a temp */
2117 temp_arr = mk_result_sptr(func_ast, func_args, subscr, DTY(dtype + 1),
2118 lhs, &retval);
2119 if (temp_arr != 0) {
2120 mk_mem_allocate(mk_id(temp_arr), subscr, arg_gbl.std, 0);
2121 mk_mem_deallocate(mk_id(temp_arr), arg_gbl.std);
2122 }
2123 }
2124 inline_shifts(func_ast, func_args, retval);
2125 return temp_arr == 0 && lhs != 0 ? 0 : retval;
2126
2127 eoshiftcall:
2128 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2129 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 3);
2130 if (dim == 0)
2131 dim = mk_cval(1, DT_INT);
2132 nargs = 5;
2133 shift = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2134 if (A_SHAPEG(shift) == 0) {
2135 /* shift is scalar */
2136 shift = convert_int(shift, astb.bnd.dtype);
2137 /* boundary is... */
2138 if (ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2) == 0) { /* absent */
2139 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_eoshiftszca : RTE_eoshiftsz;
2140 --nargs;
2141 } else if (A_SHAPEG(ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2)) == 0) /* scalar */
2142 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_eoshiftssca : RTE_eoshiftss;
2143 else /* array */
2144 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_eoshiftsaca : RTE_eoshiftsa;
2145 } else {
2146 /* shift is array */
2147 /* boundary is... */
2148 if (ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2) == 0) { /* absent */
2149 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_eoshiftzca : RTE_eoshiftz;
2150 --nargs;
2151 } else if (A_SHAPEG(ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2)) == 0) /* scalar */
2152 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_eoshiftsca : RTE_eoshifts;
2153 else /* array */
2154 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_eoshiftca : RTE_eoshift;
2155 }
2156 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2157 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2158 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = shift;
2159 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = convert_int(dim, astb.bnd.dtype);
2160 if (nargs == 5)
2161 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 4) = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2162 goto ret_new;
2163 case I_MATMUL: /* matmul(matrix_a, matrix_b) */
2164 case I_MATMUL_TRANSPOSE: /* matmul((transpose(matrix_a), matrix_b) */
2165 return matmul(func_ast, func_args, lhs);
2166 case I_FINDLOC: /* minloc(array, [dim, mask]) */
2167 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2168 value = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2169 back = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 4);
2170 mask = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 3);
2171 mask = misalignment(srcarray, mask, arg_gbl.std);
2172 if (mask == 0)
2173 mask = mk_cval(1, DT_LOG);
2174 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2175
2176 if (DTY(A_DTYPEG(value)) == TY_CHAR || DTY(A_DTYPEG(value)) == TY_NCHAR) {
2177 temp_sptr = memsym_of_ast(value);
2178 /* e.g., pghpf_any(result, mask, dim) */
2179 if (dim == 0) {
2180 newsym = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_findlocstrs), DT_NONE);
2181 nargs = 6;
2182 /* scalar findloc, result must be replicated */
2183 /* get the temp and add the necessary statements */
2184 temp_arr = mk_maxloc_sptr(
2185 shape, DDTG(dtype) == DT_INT8 ? DT_INT8 : astb.bnd.dtype);
2186 retval = mk_id(temp_arr);
2187 /* add args */
2188 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2189 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2190 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2191 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = value;
2192 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = size_ast(temp_sptr, DTYPEG(temp_sptr));
2193 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 4) = mask;
2194 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 5) = back;
2195 goto ret_call;
2196 } else {
2197 /* pghpf_findloc(result, array, mask, dim) */
2198 rtlRtn = RTE_findlocstr;
2199 nargs = 7;
2200 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2201 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2202 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = value;
2203 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = size_ast(temp_sptr, DTYPEG(temp_sptr));
2204 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 4) = mask;
2205 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 5) = dim;
2206 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 6) = back;
2207 goto ret_new;
2208 }
2209 } else {
2210 if (dim == 0) {
2211 nargs = 5;
2212 newsym = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_findlocs), DT_NONE);
2213 /* scalar findloc, result must be replicated */
2214 /* get the temp and add the necessary statements */
2215 temp_arr = mk_maxloc_sptr(
2216 shape, DDTG(dtype) == DT_INT8 ? DT_INT8 : astb.bnd.dtype);
2217 retval = mk_id(temp_arr);
2218 /* add args */
2219 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2220 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2221 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2222 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = value;
2223 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = mask;
2224 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 4) = back;
2225 goto ret_call;
2226 } else {
2227 /* pghpf_findloc(result, array, mask, dim) */
2228 rtlRtn = RTE_findloc;
2229 nargs = 6;
2230 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2231 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2232 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = value;
2233 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = mask;
2234 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 4) = dim;
2235 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 5) = back;
2236 goto ret_new;
2237 }
2238 }
2239
2240 case I_MAXLOC: /* maxloc(array, [dim, mask]) */
2241 case I_MINLOC: /* minloc(array, [dim, mask]) */
2242 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2243 back = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 3);
2244 is_back_true = get_int_cval(sym_of_ast(back));
2245 mask = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2246 mask = misalignment(srcarray, mask, arg_gbl.std);
2247 if (mask == 0)
2248 mask = mk_cval(1, DT_LOG);
2249 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2250 if (dim == 0) {
2251 if (is_back_true) {
2252 rtlRtn = optype == I_MAXLOC ? RTE_maxlocs_b : RTE_minlocs_b;
2253 } else {
2254 rtlRtn = optype == I_MAXLOC ? RTE_maxlocs : RTE_minlocs;
2255 }
2256 newsym = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), DT_NONE);
2257 nargs = is_back_true ? 4 : 3;
2258 /* get the temp and add the necessary statements */
2259 temp_arr = mk_maxloc_sptr(shape, DDTG(dtype) == DT_INT8 ? DT_INT8
2260 : astb.bnd.dtype);
2261 retval = mk_id(temp_arr);
2262 /* add args */
2263 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2264 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2265 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2266 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mask;
2267 if (is_back_true)
2268 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = back;
2269 goto ret_call;
2270 } else {
2271 /* pghpf_minloc(result, array, mask, dim) */
2272 if (is_back_true) {
2273 rtlRtn = optype == I_MAXLOC ? RTE_maxloc_b : RTE_minloc_b;
2274 } else {
2275 rtlRtn = optype == I_MAXLOC ? RTE_maxloc : RTE_minloc;
2276 }
2277 nargs = is_back_true ? 5 : 4;
2278 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2279 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2280 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mask;
2281 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = dim;
2282 if (is_back_true)
2283 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 4) = back;
2284 goto ret_new;
2285 }
2286 case I_PACK: /* pack(array, mask, [vector]) */
2287 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2288 mask = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2289 vector = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2290
2291 if (vector == 0) {
2292 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_packzca : RTE_packz;
2293 } else {
2294 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_packca : RTE_pack;
2295 }
2296
2297 if (mask == 0)
2298 mask = mk_cval(1, DT_LOG);
2299 if (DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
2300 ast_from_len = srcarray;
2301 }
2302 if (vector == 0) {
2303 nargs = 3;
2304 /* pghpf_packz(result, array, mask) */
2305 } else {
2306 nargs = 4;
2307 /* pghpf_pack(result, array, mask, vector) */
2308 }
2309 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2310 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2311 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = mask;
2312 if (nargs == 4) {
2313 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = vector;
2314 }
2315 goto ret_new;
2316 case I_RESHAPE: /* reshape(source, shape, [pad, order]) */
2317 return reshape(func_ast, func_args, lhs);
2318 case I_SPREAD: /* spread(source, dim, ncopies) */
2319 dim = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2320 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2321 if (!A_SHAPEG(srcarray))
2322 dim = astb.i1;
2323 if (A_ALIASG(dim) != 0) {
2324 int temp_arr = rewrite_intr_allocatable(func_ast, func_args, lhs);
2325 if (temp_arr != 0) {
2326 return temp_arr;
2327 }
2328 goto ret_norm;
2329 }
2330 if (DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
2331 rtlRtn = A_SHAPEG(srcarray) == 0 ? RTE_spreadcs : RTE_spreadca;
2332 ast_from_len = srcarray;
2333 } else {
2334 rtlRtn = A_SHAPEG(srcarray) == 0 ? RTE_spreadsa : RTE_spread;
2335 }
2336 nargs = 4;
2337 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2338 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2339 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2340 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2341 goto ret_new;
2342 case I_TRANSPOSE: /* transpose(matrix) */
2343 temp_arr = rewrite_intr_allocatable(func_ast, func_args, lhs);
2344 if (temp_arr != 0) {
2345 return temp_arr;
2346 }
2347 goto ret_norm;
2348 case I_UNPACK: /* unpack(vector, mask, field) */
2349 rtlRtn = DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_unpackca : RTE_unpack;
2350 nargs = 4;
2351 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2352
2353 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2354 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2355 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1);
2356 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2);
2357 goto ret_new;
2358 case I_TRANSFER: /* transfer(source, mold [, size]) */
2359 /* If the result is an array, then the size is either taken
2360 * from the size argument, or is based on the size of the source
2361 * and the mold.
2362 */
2363 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2364 mask = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 1); /* mold */
2365 vector = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 2); /* size */
2366 /* pghpf_transfer(result, src, sizeof(src), sizeof(mold)) */
2367 nargs = 4;
2368 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2369 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = srcarray;
2370 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = size_ast(sym_of_ast(mask), DDTG(A_DTYPEG(mask)));
2371 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = size_ast_of(srcarray, DDTG(A_DTYPEG(srcarray)));
2372 /* get the name of the library routine */
2373 newsym = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_transfer), DT_NONE);
2374 /* get the temp and add the necessary statements */
2375 if (shape) {
2376 /* need to put this into a temp */
2377 temp_arr = mk_result_sptr(func_ast, func_args, subscr, DTY(dtype + 1), 0,
2378 &retval);
2379 /* add temp_arr as argument */
2380 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2381 if (ALLOCG(temp_arr)) {
2382 int ddtg = DDTG(A_DTYPEG(mask));
2383 if (ddtg == DT_ASSCHAR || ddtg == DT_ASSNCHAR || ddtg == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
2384 ddtg == DT_DEFERNCHAR)
2385 mk_mem_allocate(mk_id(temp_arr), subscr, arg_gbl.std, mask);
2386 else
2387 mk_mem_allocate(mk_id(temp_arr), subscr, arg_gbl.std, 0);
2388 mk_mem_deallocate(mk_id(temp_arr), arg_gbl.std);
2389 }
2390 } else if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR
2391 || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR
2392 ) {
2393 retval = alloc_char_temp(dtype, "transfer", ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2),
2394 arg_gbl.std, 0);
2395 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2396 } else if ((DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR
2397 || DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR
2398 ) &&
2399 A_ALIASG(DTY(dtype + 1)) == 0) {
2400 /* the result has adjustable length */
2401 retval = alloc_char_temp(dtype, "transfer", ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2),
2402 arg_gbl.std, 0);
2403 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2404 } else {
2405 /* need to put this into a scalar temp */
2406 int temp_sclr = sym_get_scalar("transfer", "r", dtype);
2407 /* add temp_sclr as argument */
2408 retval = mk_id(temp_sclr);
2409 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2410 }
2411 goto ret_call;
2412
2413 case I_ADJUSTL: /* adjustl(string) */
2414 case I_ADJUSTR: /* adjustr(string) */
2415 if (optype == I_ADJUSTL) {
2416 rtlRtn = DTY(DDTG(dtype)) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_adjustla : RTE_nadjustl;
2417 root = "adjl";
2418 } else {
2419 rtlRtn = DTY(DDTG(dtype)) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_adjustra : RTE_nadjustr;
2420 root = "adjr";
2421 }
2422 newsym = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), DT_INT);
2423 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2424 /* len = RTE_[n]adjust[lr](string) */
2425 nargs = 2;
2426 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2427 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = arg1;
2428
2429 /* the result has adjustable length */
2430 forall_depnd_intrin = arg_gbl.inforall && charintr_arg_forall_depnd(arg1);
2431 if (forall_depnd_intrin) {
2432 /* ADJUST[rl] in a FORALL, need an array temp subscr'd using
2433 * the subscripts on the original assign LHS */
2434 ast = A_LOPG(arg1);
2435 shape = A_SHAPEG(ast);
2436 retval = get_charintrin_temp(ast, root);
2437 retval = mk_subscr_copy(retval, A_ASDG(arg1), A_DTYPEG(ast));
2438 } else {
2439 ast = arg1;
2440 retval = get_charintrin_temp(ast, root);
2441 }
2442
2443 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSTR) {
2444 /* We need to preserve the substring argument unless the
2445 * string that we're taking the substring of is adjustable.
2446 */
2447 switch (A_DTYPEG(A_LOPG(ast))) {
2448 case DT_ASSCHAR:
2449 case DT_ASSNCHAR:
2450 case DT_DEFERCHAR:
2451 case DT_DEFERNCHAR:
2452 break;
2453 default:
2454 /*
2455 * First, create a temporary and then propagate the substring
2456 * expression normalized to 1 to the temporary. Normalization
2457 * is required since for adjustr(aaa(ii:jj)), the temp space
2458 * requirement will be computed as (jj - ii + 1) and the result
2459 * will be expressed as tmp(ii:jj), thus exceeded the space
2460 * allocated. Need to express the result as tmp(1:sz), where
2461 * sz is 'jj - ii + 1'.
2462 */
2463 if (A_LEFTG(ast) && A_LEFTG(ast) != astb.i1) {
2464 int r = A_RIGHTG(ast);
2465 int temp_ast;
2466 if (!r) {
2467 r = string_expr_length(A_LOPG(ast));
2468 }
2469 temp_ast = mk_binop(OP_SUB, r, A_LEFTG(ast), DT_INT);
2470 temp_ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, temp_ast, astb.i1, DT_INT);
2471 retval = mk_substr(retval, 0, temp_ast, A_DTYPEG(retval));
2472 } else
2473 retval = mk_substr(retval, 0, A_RIGHTG(ast), A_DTYPEG(retval));
2474 }
2475 }
2476
2477 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2478 if (shape) {
2479 ADSC *ad;
2480 dtnew = get_array_dtype(SHD_NDIM(shape), DT_INT);
2481 ad = AD_DPTR(dtnew);
2482 for (i = 0; i < (int)SHD_NDIM(shape); i++) {
2483 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = AD_LWAST(ad, i) = SHD_LWB(shape, i);
2484 AD_UPBD(ad, i) = AD_UPAST(ad, i) = SHD_UPB(shape, i);
2485 AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i) = mk_extent(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i), i);
2486 }
2487 temp_sptr = get_adjlr_arr_temp(dtnew);
2488 astnew = mk_id(temp_sptr);
2489 ast = mk_func_node(A_INTR, mk_id(newsym), nargs, newargt);
2490 A_OPTYPEP(ast, optype);
2491 } else {
2492 dtnew = DT_INT;
2493 astnew = mk_id(get_temp(DT_INT));
2494 ast = mk_func_node(A_FUNC, mk_id(newsym), nargs, newargt);
2495 }
2496
2497 A_DTYPEP(ast, dtnew);
2498 A_SHAPEP(ast, shape);
2499
2500 if (forall_depnd_intrin) {
2501 /* ADJUST[rl] in a FORALL, generate the a FORALL that assigns
2502 * the ADJUST[rl] to the subscr'd temp */
2503 int newforall;
2504 int forall = STD_AST(arg_gbl.std);
2505 astnew = mk_subscr_copy(astnew, A_ASDG(arg1), A_DTYPEG(ast));
2506
2507 ast = mk_assn_stmt(astnew, ast, dtnew);
2508 newforall = mk_stmt(A_FORALL, 0);
2509 A_LISTP(newforall, A_LISTG(forall));
2510 A_IFEXPRP(newforall, 0);
2511 A_IFSTMTP(newforall, ast);
2512 add_stmt_before(newforall, arg_gbl.std);
2513 } else {
2514 ast = mk_assn_stmt(astnew, ast, dtnew);
2515 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
2516 }
2517 return retval;
2518
2519 case I_TRIM: /* trim(string) */
2520 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2521 /* len = RTE_[n]trim(string) */
2522 nargs = 2;
2523 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2524 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = arg1;
2525 rtlRtn = DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_trima : RTE_ntrim;
2526 newsym = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), DT_INT);
2527 /* the result has adjustable length */
2528 if (arg_gbl.inforall && charintr_arg_forall_depnd(arg1)) {
2529 /* The call to RTE_trim must be in
2530 * a FORALL and the result(s) must be arrays */
2531 int forall = STD_AST(arg_gbl.std);
2532 int newforall;
2533 ADSC *ad;
2534
2535 ast = A_LOPG(arg1);
2536 retval = get_charintrin_temp(ast, "trim");
2537 retval = mk_subscr_copy(retval, A_ASDG(arg1), A_DTYPEG(ast));
2538 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2539
2540 shape = A_SHAPEG(ast);
2541 dtnew = get_array_dtype(SHD_NDIM(shape), DT_INT);
2542 ad = AD_DPTR(dtnew);
2543 for (i = 0; i < (int)SHD_NDIM(shape); i++) {
2544 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = AD_LWAST(ad, i) = SHD_LWB(shape, i);
2545 AD_UPBD(ad, i) = AD_UPAST(ad, i) = SHD_UPB(shape, i);
2546 AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i) = mk_extent(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i), i);
2547 }
2548 temp_sptr = get_adjlr_arr_temp(dtnew);
2549 astnew = mk_id(temp_sptr);
2550
2551 mk_mem_allocate(astnew, 0, arg_gbl.std, 0);
2552 mk_mem_deallocate(astnew, arg_gbl.std);
2553 astnew = mk_subscr_copy(astnew, A_ASDG(arg1), DT_INT);
2554
2555 ast = mk_func_node(A_INTR, mk_id(newsym), nargs, newargt);
2556 A_DTYPEP(ast, DT_INT);
2557 A_SHAPEP(ast, 0);
2558 A_OPTYPEP(ast, I_TRIM);
2559 ast = mk_assn_stmt(astnew, ast, DT_INT);
2560
2561 retval = mk_substr(retval, 0, astnew, A_DTYPEG(retval));
2562
2563 newforall = mk_stmt(A_FORALL, 0);
2564 A_LISTP(newforall, A_LISTG(forall));
2565 A_IFEXPRP(newforall, 0);
2566 A_IFSTMTP(newforall, ast);
2567 add_stmt_before(newforall, arg_gbl.std);
2568 } else {
2569 int len_ast;
2570 retval = get_charintrin_temp(arg1, "trim");
2571 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = retval;
2572 temp_sptr = A_SPTRG(retval);
2573 if (DTY(DTYPEG(temp_sptr)) == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
2574 DTY(DTYPEG(temp_sptr)) == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
2575 len_ast = get_len_of_deferchar_ast(retval);
2576 } else if (SCG(temp_sptr) == SC_BASED) {
2577 len_ast = mk_id(CVLENG(temp_sptr));
2578 } else {
2579 int len_sptr = get_next_sym(SYMNAME(temp_sptr), "cl");
2580 STYPEP(len_sptr, ST_VAR);
2581 DTYPEP(len_sptr, DT_INT);
2582 SCP(len_sptr, symutl.sc);
2583 len_ast = mk_id(len_sptr);
2584 }
2585 /* add call to function; function returns the len */
2586 ast = mk_func_node(A_FUNC, mk_id(newsym), nargs, newargt);
2587 A_DTYPEP(ast, DT_INT);
2588 A_SHAPEP(ast, 0);
2589 ast = mk_assn_stmt(len_ast, ast, DT_INT);
2590 add_stmt_before(ast, arg_gbl.std);
2591 retval = mk_substr(retval, 0, len_ast, dtype);
2592 }
2593 return retval;
2594
2595 case I_DATE_AND_TIME:
2596 rtlRtn = RTE_dandta;
2597 is_icall = FALSE;
2598 nargs = 4;
2599 goto opt_common;
2600 case I_SYSTEM_CLOCK:
2601 rtlRtn = RTE_sysclk;
2602 is_icall = FALSE;
2603 nargs = 3;
2604 goto opt_common;
2605 case I_CPU_TIME:
2606 is_icall = FALSE;
2607 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2608 if (DTYG(A_DTYPEG(arg1)) == TY_DBLE)
2609 rtlRtn = RTE_cpu_timed;
2610#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
2611 else if (DTYG(A_DTYPEG(arg1)) == TY_QUAD)
2612 rtlRtn = RTE_cpu_timeq;
2613#endif
2614 else
2615 rtlRtn = RTE_cpu_time;
2616 nargs = 1;
2617 goto opt_common;
2618 case I_RANDOM_NUMBER:
2619 is_icall = FALSE;
2620 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2621 if (DTYG(A_DTYPEG(arg1)) == TY_DBLE)
2622 rtlRtn = RTE_rnumd;
2623#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
2624 else if (DTYG(A_DTYPEG(arg1)) == TY_QUAD)
2625 rtlRtn = RTE_rnumq;
2626#endif
2627 else
2628 rtlRtn = RTE_rnum;
2629 nargs = 1;
2630 goto opt_common;
2631 case I_RANDOM_SEED:
2632 rtlRtn = RTE_rseed;
2633 is_icall = FALSE;
2634 nargs = 3;
2635 opt_common:
2636 newargt = mk_argt(nargs);
2637 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
2638 if (ARGT_ARG(func_args, i) == 0)
2639 ARGT_ARG(newargt, i) = astb.ptr0;
2640 else
2641 ARGT_ARG(newargt, i) = ARGT_ARG(func_args, i);
2642 }
2643 newsym = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), DT_NONE);
2644 retval = 0;
2645 goto ret_call;
2646 case I_PRESENT:
2647 /* present(a) will be present(a$b) a$b base of dummy */
2648 srcarray = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2649 if (A_TYPEG(srcarray) == A_ID && (sptr = A_SPTRG(srcarray)) &&
2650 SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY &&
2651 !HCCSYMG(sptr) && /* compiler's PRESENT is correct */
2652 STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ARRAY) {
2653 if (!normalize_bounds(sptr) || needs_redim(sptr)) {
2654 sptr = NEWARGG(sptr);
2655 }
2656 assert(sptr, "rewrite_func_ast: no formal symbol", func_ast, 3);
2657 ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0) = mk_id(sptr);
2658 }
2659 goto ret_norm;
2660 case I_SECNDS:
2661 nargs = 1;
2662 is_icall = FALSE;
2663 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2664 rtlRtn = DTY(A_DTYPEG(arg1)) == TY_DBLE ? RTE_secndsd : RTE_secnds;
2665 newsym = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), dtype);
2666 retval = mk_func_node(A_FUNC, mk_id(newsym), nargs, func_args);
2667 A_DTYPEP(retval, dtype);
2668 A_SHAPEP(retval, 0);
2669 return retval;
2670 case I_TIME:
2671 is_icall = FALSE;
2672 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2673 rtlRtn = DTY(A_DTYPEG(arg1)) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_ftimea : RTE_ftimew;
2674 goto sub_common;
2675 case I_DATE:
2676 is_icall = FALSE;
2677 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2678 rtlRtn = DTY(A_DTYPEG(arg1)) == TY_CHAR ? RTE_datea : RTE_datew;
2679 goto sub_common;
2680 case I_IDATE:
2681 is_icall = FALSE;
2682 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(func_args, 0);
2683 rtlRtn = DTY(A_DTYPEG(arg1)) == TY_SINT ? RTE_idate : RTE_jdate;
2684 goto sub_common;
2685 case I_LASTVAL:
2686 rtlRtn = RTE_lastval;
2687 is_icall = FALSE;
2688 goto sub_common;
2689 case I_REDUCE_SUM:
2690 rtlRtn = RTE_global_sum;
2691 is_icall = TRUE;
2692 goto sub_common;
2693 case I_REDUCE_PRODUCT:
2694 rtlRtn = RTE_global_product;
2695 is_icall = TRUE;
2696 goto sub_common;
2697 case I_REDUCE_ANY:
2698 rtlRtn = RTE_global_any;
2699 is_icall = TRUE;
2700 goto sub_common;
2701 case I_REDUCE_ALL:
2702 rtlRtn = RTE_global_all;
